title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve gelatine in clam juice.
Add clams and shrimp.
Allow the gelatine to set firm.
Add the following to the gelatine after firm:
cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion, celery and lemon juice. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend on low speed the buttermilk and pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
You can layer the fruit if you like or just add it all in and fold carefully so as not to break it up.

title: cherry jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Combine all ingredients except juice and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 10 x 14 x 2 inch pan and bake for 45 minutes.
While still hot, prick cake with fork and pour pineapple juice over the top.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: In a skillet, brown 1 pound ground beef. In a cake pan, spread one layer of refried beans, one layer of shredded cheese, one layer of ground beef, one layer of salsa and one layer of sour cream. Top with more shredded cheese,
onion (optional) and black olives. Use as much or as little as you wish. You can not do this wrong. Dip with Fritos or Tostitos.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, water and butter into 2-quart Corning Ware dish.
Bring to a boil until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Make hole in center of mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Mix as you would cornbread; do not beat.
Cook in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican salsa dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with Doritos.
Best if made the day before.

title: sherry's green beans
directions: Roll 4 or 5 green beans in a single slice of bacon.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar and pour over bean/bacon rolls.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder.
Bake, covered, at 375° for one hour.
Uncover and broil for five minutes.

title: sausage chili
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef and sausage until browned; drain fat.
Transfer meat mixture to crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.

title: cheese cake
directions: Lay rolls out flat side to the middle.
Mix the cream cheese, lemon juice, flour, sugar and egg together.
Pour onto the rolls and fold.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade noodles with chicken or beef
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in sifted flour.
Knead well.
Roll out on floured board until very thin.
Then sprinkle with flour and roll up like jelly roll.
Slice thin and then shake out.
Have chicken or beef broth seasoned and boiling.
Drop in noodles; cook 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Place cucumbers and onion between paper towels to absorb moisture.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or party bread.

title: best ever wilted spinach salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Put bacon and all ingredients in saucepan, except spinach.
Heat on medium until thick, stirring often.
Pour over washed spinach.
Mix well; serve immediately.
May serve with croutons.

title: lavonne watt's cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and juice from can of peaches.
Pour over oleo in casserole.
Place sliced peaches on top of batter.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients come to a boil; add eggs.
Add cornstarch and let thicken.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Coarse-grind pork with
1/2-inch plate.
Mix ingredients well by hand, then grind again, using 1/8-inch plate.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix crust as you would pie dough. Press into 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 10-15 minutes).

title: garden fresh relish
directions: Put tomatoes, onions, peppers and cabbage in a large saucepan. Tie spices in cheesecloth; drop in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables, stirring until well mixed. Bring to a boil and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Makes 5 pints.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Cut up bell pepper, onion and chicken breasts.
Sear chicken in 2 teaspoons oil.
Add paprika, salt and pepper, stirring occasionally for about 4 minutes.
Add bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook about 4 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, chicken broth and rice.
Cover and simmer until rice is done or longer.
Serve in warmed flour tortillas with grated Cheddar cheese and picante sauce.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Drain the chicken; cool and shred.

title: buttermilk pie 3
directions: Mix sugar, flour and 1/2 cup buttermilk. Add eggs and rest of milk. Then fold in butter and vanilla. Pour into pie shell (deep). Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: squash casserole(good "what should i bring?" dish)
directions: In large saucepan, cook first three ingredients until almost tender, about 4 minutes.
Add soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir until blended.
Add stuffing mix, toss to coat and transfer mixture to buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350° until bubbling and browned on top.

title: finger drumsticks
directions: Cut off tips of wings and discard.
Divide each wing in half by cutting through joint with a sharp knife.
Place in a single layer
on
broiler pan rack.
Bake in hot oven (400°), turning once, 30 minutes.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger and pepper in a small saucepan; stir in water, lemon juice and soy
sauce. Cook,
stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils 3 minutes.
Brush part over chicken wings.
Continue baking, turning and
brushing
several
times
with
remaining lemon mixture, 40 minutes
or until richly glazed.
When ready to serve, place in a chafing
dish or keep hot server.
Makes 12 servings.

title: muffins
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Combine milk, egg and Crisco.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients until moistened.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix flour with water; stir until smooth, then add to the preceding ingredients and cook slowly until thickens.
Cool, then add vanilla.
Add extra milk if needed to fill freezer.
You may also use fresh fruits.

title: vidalia onion casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Melt stick margarine and saute onions until clear and tender. Grease 2-quart casserole dish with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Line dish with cracker crumbs, reserving 3 tablespoons for topping. Add onions and cream of mushroom soup in alternate layers until dish is full.
Cover top of casserole with beaten eggs and pour milk over top.
Sprinkle grated cheese and remaining cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream, 1/2 of whipped topping and vanilla.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with remaining whipped topping.
Makes 1 medium dessert.
Best refrigerated for 24 hours.

title: marie's cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add sugar and vanilla; fold in sour cream.
Spray pan with cooking spray.
Pour into 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until top is golden brown. Let cool.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Butter a flat casserole and alternate a layer of 1/4-inch bread cubes and a layer of cheese, ending with cheese.
Pour melted butter over all.

title: crunchy health bars
directions: Bring
first
3 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 7 to 10 minutes, until thickened.
Remove from heat and add
other ingredients.
Mix
well.
Turn
into
sprayed
8 x 8-inch pan and chill.
Cut into bars and refrigerate.

title: cabbage rolls (glumpkies)
directions: Steam cabbage until soft. Combine all ingredients. Put in refrigerator until all milk is absorbed. Put a tablespoon or so in leaf, roll up. Place seam side down. Mix can chicken broth and a can of tomato soup. Put brown sugar on first, about 2 tablespoons, pour broth and soup mix over cabbage rolls. Cover with foil. Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour or until cabbage is soft. In preheated oven. Baste a couple of times.

title: cheese and fruit salad
directions: Just before serving, in medium bowl, combine mayonnaise with lemon juice.
Stir in apple, pear and cheese.
Makes 2 salad servings.

title: famous pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add salt, syrup, nuts and well beaten eggs.
Mix together and pour into unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: taco pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crust according to directions on package.
Prebake pizza crust about 5 minutes and remove from oven. Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco sauce to meat and mix.
Spread over crust.
Then layer refried beans and cheese.
Return to oven and bake until crust is brown and cheese is melted.
Serve with shredded lettuce, tomatoes, onions and sour cream.

title: cranberry apple pear relish
directions: Pare, halve, core and chop apples and pears.
Put in a medium saucepan.
Add washed cranberries, sugar, water and horseradish. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer about 15 minutes, or until fruits are tender.
Cool.
Store in covered containers in refrigerator for 2 or 3 weeks.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: peanut butter candy roll
directions: Blend together margarine and 2 cups of sugar.
Gradually add remaining sugar and milk, blending well until mixture is consistency of pie dough.
Sprinkle area with 10x sugar and roll out 1/2 of dough into rectangle about 1/8-inch thick.
Spread entire surface with peanut butter.
Starting at longest edge, roll up like a jelly roll.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In skillet saute onion in oil until tender.
Stir in chili powder; cook 1 minute.
Add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon salt, heat to boiling.
Reduce and simmer 10 minutes or until slightly thickens.
In large bowl, mix chicken, green chilies, sour cream.
Place about 1/3 cup chicken mix along one edge of each tortilla; roll jelly-roll style.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon half of tomato sauce in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of each cheese.
Place enchiladas seam side down on top of cheese; pour over rest of sauce then sprinkle cheese on top. Bake uncovered 30 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: egg salad
directions: Mash and mix the entire egg with seasonings.
Serve as a salad on a lettuce leaf with tomato wedges or serve as filling for a sandwich.
Yield:
1 serving.
Carbohydrate 0 g, protein 6 g, fat 6 g, calories 78.
One serving = one meat medium fat exchange, 2 bread starch exchange.

title: eggs fantastic
directions: Saute onion, sausage and mushrooms; drain.
Mix eggs and sour cream in blender.
Grease glass pan.
Cook eggs 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Add hot sauce and sausage mixture.
Slice cheese and lay on Cheddar and Monterey Jack, then Velveeta.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes.
May be done a day ahead.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Cream together Crisco, brown sugar, peanut butter, salt and egg. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Mix well; shape into 1 inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: "light" beef stroganoff
directions: Slice steak across grain into thick strips about 1/8-inch wide and 3-inches long.
Wash and slice mushrooms; cook beef strips, mushrooms and onion in nonstick frying pan until beef is lightly browned.
Add broth, water, ketchup and pepper.
Cook and simmer until beef is tender about 45 minutes.
Mix flour with about 1/4 cup buttermilk until smooth.
Add remaining buttermilk.
Stir into beef mixture.
Cook stirring constantly until thickened.
Serve over noodles.
Makes 4 servings at 255 calories per serving.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Chill all ingredients ahead of time.
Mix and serve.

title: hot and spicy chicken
directions: Bake chicken for 1 hour in mixture.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 3-inch strips, then in quarters.
Cook in small amount of salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients and cook 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove cinnamon stick and cloves.
Pour over cooled carrots.
Prepare at least 8 hours before eating.

title: kabob marinade
directions: Combine all marinade ingredients.
Add kabob meats and vegetables.
Let stand for about 2 hours.
Use marinade for basting sauce when grilling kabobs.

title: oven barbecued brisket
directions: Heat 8 ounces Eckrich, sliced, 1/2 cup frozen peas in 1 can golden mushroom soup mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Serve over hot noodles!

title: pineapple frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Whip until smooth.
Place in a container that you can freeze.
Freeze, then serve cool.
Can be made one day or several days ahead.

title: no fuss chicken
directions: Mix together. Pour over chicken breasts. Bake, covered, 20 minutes and uncovered 20 minutes more at 350°.

title: low-fat apple upside-down cake
directions: Coat a 9-inch round pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread the apple juice concentrate over the bottom of the skillet and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Arrange the apple slices in a circular pattern over the brown sugar.
Set aside.

title: m&m's plain chocolate cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cream thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients and gradually add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
approximately 6 dozen cookies.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Combine in 1 1/2-quart jar with tight fitting lid.
Shake well.
Refrigerate; keeps for 3 weeks.
Shake well before using.

title: pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium heat. Add onion; cook 2 minutes or until tender. Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until well blended. Gradually stir in broth and milk, cooking and stirring until bubbly and thickened. Add chicken or turkey and mixed vegetables; mix well. Remove from heat. Spoon mixture into crust-lined pan. Top with second crust; seal edges and flute. Cut slits in several places in top crust. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: seafood salad
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and cool.
Mix with first five ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise with milk to a creamy sauce.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate.
Chill for a day or two.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, then dry ingredients, alternately with water.
Add vanilla.
Add 1/2 stick butter.
Bake in small muffin pan after putting 1/2 teaspoon melted butter in bottom of each tin.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes.
While still hot, dip in glaze.
Dry on rack or waxed paper.

title: sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine milk, margarine, 1/4 cup sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add yeast mixture, egg and 1/2 cup flour, then rest of flour.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl and turn.
Let rise for 1 hour.

title: radish and cream cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese, butter, celery salt, paprika and Worcestershire sauce together until smooth.
Stir in radishes and onions.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Spread on rye crisp.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: aunt frances simmons' pear honey
directions: Combine pears and sugar, cook 1 hour. Add crushed pineapple and cook a little longer. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: coconut cream pies
directions: Cook until starts to thicken; add coconut and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Let cool.
Do not let it set. Add drained mandarin oranges and sherbet.
Mix well.
Put in mold and jell.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat until tender. Stir in next 6 ingredients. Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Spoon 1/3 of sauce mixture in bottom of a lightly greased 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Layer with 1/3 of tortillas, 1/2 of chicken and 1 cup cheese. Repeat all layers until used all, ending with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and the shortening.
Add the bananas and cream all together.
Add the eggs, one at a time, mixing after each one. Sift together the flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg.
Add the banana mixture and blend thoroughly.
Lastly, add the pecans.

title: deer steak
directions: Flour steak; brown in skillet.
Add sliced bell pepper and chopped onion.
Add water and simmer approximately 20 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Thaw broccoli and place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Cook onion in 1/4 cup butter for 5 minutes.
Blend the flour, salt and water. Add to onion and butter mixture.
Stir cheese into mixture and blend until smooth.
Add this to broccoli.
Pour beaten eggs over top.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs well.
Drain fruit cocktail. Add soda to the juice from the fruit.
Add the flour to the egg and sugar mixture alternately with soda and juice mixture.
Add fruit cocktail and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until done.
Frost in pan while hot with 3/4 cup sugar and Pet milk boiled 2 minutes and flake coconut added.
Pour over cake.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Melt margarine; then add sugar, eggs, pineapple and coconut. Pour batter into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until pie is firm and brown.

title: jumbo chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add walnuts, pecans, chocolate chunks and white chocolate chips.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls 3 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Flatten cookies to about 3 inches round.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.
Serve.

title: reese's candy
directions: Combine sugar and peanut butter; mix well.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Layer 8 ounces of chocolate, then spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt remaining 8 ounces chocolate bar in top of double boiler; spread on top of peanut mixture.
Chill until firm enough to cut.
Cut into bars.

title: peach bread
directions: Blend all ingredients until moistened.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May be used for muffins; bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Place 1 layer of chicken, 1/2 of the sauce (combine last 4 ingredients for sauce), 1/2 of the tortillas and 1/2 of the onion and cheese in casserole and repeat for 2nd layer with cheese on top.
Bake at 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add slowly the Cool Whip and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spoon filling into prepared crusts. Freeze at least 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish with chocolate shavings.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Set oven to 375°.
Soften margarine, then cream in sugar. Add egg and pumpkin; mix well. Mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, salt and cloves a little at a time.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chinese beef
directions: Heat oil in pan and brown steak.
Remove from pan.
Lower heat to medium and if using onion, saute until soft.
If not using onion, leave meat in pan and add broth
or soup, soy sauce, ginger and carrots.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add celery and green pepper and cook 15 minutes more.
In small cup, blend cornstarch and water.
Add to beef mixture.
Increase heat and stir until it thickens.
Drain bean sprouts and add to beef.
Heat until sprouts are hot.
Serve over rice.

title: dump cake
directions: In cake pan, layer cherries, pineapple, cake mix, butter, pecans and coconut.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine Cookie Crumb Crust Mix and 1/4 cup melted butter or margarine.
Press into an unbuttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, 1 cup butter or margarine and powdered sugar; beat 10 to 15 minutes, until smooth.
Spread over crust mix that is in pan.
Slice bananas evenly over top of mixture.
Spread crushed, drained pineapple over bananas evenly. Top with whipped cream; sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: candied cucumber rings
directions: Combine cucumbers, lime and 8 1/2 quarts of water in a large container; let stand for 24 hours.
Drain, then rinse in clear water.
Cover with water; let stand for 3 hours, then drain.

title: aunt madeline's caramel corn
directions: Combine butter, sugars, corn syrup and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour mixture over popcorn and nuts, coating well.
Pour mix into 9 x 13-inch shallow baking pans.
Bake at 250° until mixture is dry, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Stir again after removing to break clumps.

title: malted milk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, malted milk powder, soda and salt; mix well.
Set aside.
Blend sugars, vanilla and condensed milk; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and chocolate chips and blend at low speed.
Do not overmix.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 24 to 25 minutes or until cookies are slightly brown along edges.
Transfer cookies to cool surface immediately.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: celery pinwheels
directions: Cut base from celery bunch.
Separate, wash and dry stalks. Fill each stalk with tangy cheese spread.
Press stalks together in shape of original bunch and tie with strings.
Chill. To serve, cut into 1/4 to 1/2 inch slices.

title: potato pan rolls
directions: Boil potatoes in 1 1/2 cups water until tender; drain. Reserve 1 cup liquid.
Mash potatoes and set aside 1 cup to cool. Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm potato liquid.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, butter, honey, oil, eggs, salt and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth 6 to 8 minutes. Add enough flour to make dough.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Shape into rolls. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: spuds with a twist
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Form uncooked ground chuck into 1-inch round balls.
Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place ground chuck balls and quartered potatoes in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Sprinkle package of Lipton onion soup mix over top.
Pour 1/4 cup vegetable oil over the top of all ingredients.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium size pot.
Cook over medium-low heat until thick.
Will scorch easily.
Pour into 2 baked crusts and put on meringue.
Makes 2 large pies.
Use egg whites for meringue.
Brown in oven at 350°.
Add one tablespoon of sugar per egg for meringue.

title: aunt lucy's butterscotch torte
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan the butter, flour and pecans.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Dust the chicken in mixture of flour, salt and oregano.
Brown lightly.
One at a time, saute the vegetables.
Place chicken pieces in a casserole dish and place the sauteed vegetables on top.
Add the orange juice and wine.
Cover and bake at 350° at least 2 hours, basting occasionally.
Serve with rice prepared as follows:
To cooked rice, add 1 stick margarine, 1/2 cup salted, chopped peanuts, cinnamon and ginger.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch square microwave dish, layer soft cream cheese on bottom (microwave 1 minute to soften).
Layer chili, then salsa to cover over chili.
Spread shredded cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave until cheese melts (3 or 4 minutes). Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a paper bag. Moisten potato quarters with water.
Shake a few at a time in the bag to coat well with cheese and flour mixture.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13 baking pan.
Place potatoes in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour, turning once during baking.
When golden brown, remove from oven and sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: the world's best caramel candy
directions: In deep saucepan mix sugar and syrup.
Stir until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Cook to 270° on a candy thermometer without stirring.
Slowly add 1 cup warm cream while mixture never stops boiling.
Cook to 250° stirring frequently.

title: santa claus whiskers
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Add flour, then nuts, then cherries.
Form into 2 rolls and roll in coconut. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill overnight.
Slice cookies off roll and bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken with tart orange sauce
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper. Fry in a large skillet in 2 teaspoons oil.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: In large pot, combine water, cabbage, bacon, carrots and the dry potatoes and sauce mix.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Combine the milk and cornstarch; add to soup along with green beans.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until beans are tender.
Fast, easy and great tasting!

title: candied yams
directions: Cut in half, then 4 equal sizes.
(I just cut them equally.) Place in boiler; add water to cover.
Add granulated sugar and butter or margarine.
Cook on medium, uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes until done and liquid has turned to syrup.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Leave in refrigerator until set.

title: quick party peas
directions: Shake dry onion soup into drained peas.
Add enough butter to season.
Heat slowly in casserole.

title: hard apple cider
directions: Wait until near Thanksgiving and get the last of the fresh local pressed, unfiltered unpasteurized natural cider, preferably made from a mix of the late fall apples.
Get about 1/3 of the water hot on the stove and add all the sugar, keep the fire on high until all the sugar is dissolved.
Add water if needed to dissolve all the sugar and get it boiling or near so.
Turn the fire off and stir in the juice of a fresh lemon or lime.
Let cool enough to handle.
Pour a gallon of cider in the big bottle, then the sugar water, the packets of wine yeast, then enough cider to fill to within about 6-inches from the neck.
Stopper bottle with lock or balloon and leave in the basement near to but not next to the furnace.
Save extra water and cider in the refrigerator.
After 7 to 10 days, top off the bottle with cider first, then if needed with the rest of the water, to the bottle neck.
Reseal with the lock or balloon.
Now the hard part, wait until Easter to drink. Siphon off to drink as "needed" without disturbing the sediment, then reseal, it does not need refrigeration.
Enjoy this "nectar from heaven" with some "good friends" and think about doubling the recipe for next year.
Makes 5 gallons.
(Recipe may be reduced or increased by proportional amounts.)

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in sheet cake pan.
While hot, punch holes in cake and pour cream of coconut over.
Afterwards, pour Eagle Brand milk over.
Let cool completely and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Cake should be made at least 2 to 3 days prior to serving.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza pie
directions: Mix together sour cream, garlic powder, salt, & oregano. Using 9x12 pan, spread above mixture on evenly. Add pizza sauce. Top pizza sauce with onion & green pepper. Top veggies with pepperoni. Bake at 350° covered for 15-20 minutes then uncover and add 10 more minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: steamed broccoli with basil butter
directions: If using fresh broccoli, clean well and cut into bite size pieces.
Steam fresh or frozen broccoli until barely tender, keeping the bright green color.
In a small pan, melt butter and stir in basil.
Allow basil to cook in butter over very low heat for about 5 minutes. Just before serving, toss the broccoli gently with the basil butter.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: In large saucepan, heat first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Add crabmeat; heat through.

title: tangy barbecued chicken(has citrus-like tang)
directions: Wash chicken and drain on absorbent paper.
Combine all the remaining ingredients and marinate chicken for at least 1/2 hour before barbecuing, turning several times.
Chicken can marinate in refrigerator all day if you wish.
Barbecue over moderate heat for 30 minutes, turning frequently, and watching closely.
It may also be broiled in oven broiler.
Yields 4 servings.

title: many way meat balls
directions: *Cream of vegetable, cream of mushroom, cream of celery or Cheddar cheese soup.

title: lola's pasta salad
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Add dressing, cucumber, onion and tomatoes, mixing well.
Add seasonings to taste and mix again. Chill several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle a little Salad Seasoning on top and add cheese before serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water as directed on package.
When congealed, add sour cream, pineapple and nuts.

title: cherry crescents(low-fat)
directions: Beat cream cheese, 4 packs of sweetener and 1/2 teaspoon almond flavoring.
Unroll dough into large rectangle. Close separations. Spread cream cheese mixture to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle on chopped cherries. Roll up and pinch ends closed. Bake at 350° for 17 to 18 minutes.

title: linda's pot pie
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Add with mushrooms corn, gluten and mushroom soup.
Season to taste.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: indian stew
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 450°.

title: mexican kisses
directions: Cream together margarine, powdered sugar and flour.
Add vanilla,
salt and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch size balls.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes or less.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix together powdered sugar and cocoa.
Cut butter into small pieces and put over top.
Pour in milk, not stirring.
Microwave 4-5 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Let cool completely and cut into squares.

title: wassail
directions: Heat juices. Tie spices in cheesecloth.
Add spice bag to heated juices and leave for about 10 minutes.
Remove spice bag and serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and applesauce.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add water, then raisins. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix together in that order. Yield: 7 gallons.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream together softened margarine and sugar for 20 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add plain flour.
Add lemon extract. Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: onion pork chops
directions: Combine
soup mix with bread crumbs.
Dip chops in eggs and then soup mix, making sure they are well coated.
Place in a lightly
greased
Dutch
oven.
Bake, turning once, for one hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients together.
Mix vegetables together in bowl.
Coat vegetables with sauce mixture; stir.
Remove from refrigerator about 2 hours before serving.
This salad improves with age.
Make at least 3 days ahead for
best flavor.

title: banana peppers
directions: Split peppers longways; core.
Soak 10 minutes in milk; dip in flour.
Lay aside for 10 minutes.
Dip back in milk; roll in mixture of 1/2 flour and 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Cook until brown only, in about 1 1/2-inches oil, at 375° to 400°.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oil after rolling in flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Keep potatoes, onions and carrots whole.

title: chicken sergio
directions: Flatten chicken breasts slightly.
Pour 1/4 cup wine into a heavy skillet; place over medium heat.
Add chopped shallots and sliced mushrooms into pan.
Stir.
Add parsley, tarragon and capers.
Add chicken and cook 2 to 3 minutes.

title: u. s. senate bean soup
directions: Pick over beans; wash thoroughly.
Drain and soak overnight in a large kettle with 5 quarts water.
The next day, drain liquid and measure.
Add enough water to make 2 quarts.
Add ham bone and garlic.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Add potatoes, onion and celery; simmer 1 hour longer or until beans fall apart.
Remove bone.
Cut up any meat into small pieces.
Return to soup; season to taste with salt and black pepper.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together (sugar, butter, eggs, flour, milk and vanilla) and bake at 350° until done.
When cake is cooled completely, crumble, then put crumbled cake in punch bowl. Add in layers the strawberries, then pineapple, then coconut, then pudding and Cool Whip.
Keep adding ingredients until bowl is full with Cool Whip on top.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix with sweet potatoes.
Add milk, egg and butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes or until inserted silver knife comes out clean.
Cover top with meringue, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together sugar and corn meal in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, butter, buttermilk and vanilla; blend well.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted 1-inch from center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Pie will continue to set as it cools.

title: cherry pecan torte
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Beat in cream of tartar.
Gradually add the sugar, beating on high until stiff peaks form.
Fold in crumbs, pecans, and vanilla.
Spread into a greased 13 X 9 X 2 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Spread whipped cream over the top.
Spoon pie filling over cream.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Yield:
12-15 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Place cooked zucchini in greased casserole.
Melt butter in saucepan; add cheese and sour cream. Add salt to taste.
Simmer several minutes. Add basil.
Pour over zucchini.
Cover with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: maids of honor
directions: Roll the puff pastry on floured board and use to line 12 lightly greased muffin tins.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except flaked almonds, and spoon onto pastry wells.
Sprinkle flaked almonds on top and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes, until pastry is golden brown and filling is set.

title: cheesy potato-egg casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Allow to cool to touch.
Peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices; set aside.

title: sammie's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off fat.
Mix together and simmer 2 hours.

title: mexican brunch sandwiches
directions: Slice top crust off rolls.
Hollow out leaving 1/2-inch shell. Brush with butter.
Heat beans, stir in 1/2 of cheese, fill rolls with
bean	mix,
then
sour
cream.
Sprinkle with onion; cover with
sausage.
Top with remaining cheese.	Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with salsa.

title: sauerkraut dumplings
directions: Pinch biscuits into medium size pieces and drop into boiling water.
Cook until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese in small mixing bowl.
Beat with electric beater.
Beat into the cheese next 8 ingredients until mixture is creamy.
Stir in parsley and pimento (can omit parsley at this point).
Cover and refrigerate several hours or until cheese mixture is firm enough to handle.
Shape into a ball.
Coat evenly with pecans and parsley.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm water.
Mix dough until smooth and like elastic.
Let raise 10 minutes.
Knead down.
Do this every 10 minutes for 5 times.
When it raises the sixth time, roll out about 1 1/4-inches thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or glass.
Have cookie sheets greased and sprinkle with corn meal (optional).
Let rise on cookie sheets 1 hour and 15 minutes, or 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes for own oven temperature.
Also, you can make 4 loaves.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the cold water.
Add cake mix, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Bake in stem pan 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with crushed strawberries and whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients adding potato chips last.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cheese spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Cream the cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix all other ingredients, except the pecans. Chill.
Can be rolled in a log or a ball and rolled in pecans.

title: snickers pie(low calorie, no fat)
directions: Soften ice cream in a large bowl.
Sprinkle instant pudding out of box over ice cream and mix.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Stir until blended.
Spray an 11 x 7 x 1.5-inch dish or 2 (8-inch) pie plates with Pam.
Pour mixture in desired dish and freeze.
Cut into slices.

title: candy
directions: Lay out waxed paper first.
Mix together cereals, marshmallows and peanuts.
Slowly melt chocolate, stirring constantly.
Pour over dry mixture.
Stir quickly, then spoon-drop on waxed paper.

title: ginny's christmas spice cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: low-fat layered bean dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir cream cheese well and place it in the bottom of large platter.
Spread beans over cream cheese.
Add lettuce, then cheese; pour the salsa over it all.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: egg custard pies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and flour.
Then add eggs to cream.
Then add milk gradually to blend.
Pour in 9-inch pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or less.
Depends on your oven. If pies puff up, shake pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with rolls, pressing together.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: zucchini in pecan brown butter
directions: Melt butter in a large heavy skillet over moderate heat. Cook pecans, stirring until golden brown and butter is browned. Add zucchini with salt and pepper and cook, stirring frequently, until just tender (about 10 minutes).
Serve zucchini topped with Parmesan curls. Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Heat pumpkin and add butter.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks, salt, sugar, cinnamon and ginger.
Add warm milk to heated pumpkin. Whip the egg whites until frothy and mix lightly into pumpkin. Put in pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour exactly.

title: easy dill onion bread
directions: Mix half the flour and yeast together in mixing bowl.
In saucepan, heat milk, sugar, oleo, dill weed, instant minced onion and salt.
Add to dry mixture.
Then add egg.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes at higher speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour; cover.
Let rise until double, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dried cranberry and apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small saucepan, simmer the dried cranberries, cinnamon stick and the apple juice for 10 minutes. Drain the cranberries and remove cinnamon stick.
In a small bowl, blend the flour, brown sugar, salt and the butter until mixture resembles coarse meal; toss the mixture well.
Peel, core and slice apples thin and in a buttered 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Toss them with the cranberries.
Sprinkle the brown sugar mixture over the apples and cranberries.
Bake the Crisp in the oven for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put onions in bottom of gallon jar.
Slice cucumbers and pack tightly on top.
Pour brine over cucumbers and put on lid.
Keep in refrigerator.
Ready in about a week.
Will keep for several months.

title: best brownies(very rich)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar slowly.
Melt margarine and chocolate squares over hot water and add to egg mixture.
Add flour; stir in marshmallows, nuts and chips.
Bake in greased 9-inch square pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Add milk.
Mix well. Batter should be fairly smooth.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Let cool slightly before cutting.

title: fried vegetables
directions: Dredge in flour.
Cook in hot fat over low to medium heat until tender and light brown.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Cream butter in mixer bowl until light; add sugar slowly until very light and fluffy.
Beat for 10 minutes.
In separate bowl, make meringue of the 2 egg whites and add to creamed mixture.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Do not drain strawberries.
Pecans are optional.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry.
Put batter in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tea cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Add 1 cup confectioners sugar, beating constantly.
Fold in corn flakes, coconut and lemon juice.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar and corn syrup on High for 4 minutes.
Add nuts; microwave for 3 to 5 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla; microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir quickly.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
When cool enough, stretch to desired thickness.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in Wesson oil in a large pot.
Add water.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours. Add vegetables, tomatoes and salt.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with favorite fresh vegetables.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Put pineapple in saucepan; bring to full boil.
Add jello and mix well.
Keep on simmer and add cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Add water and let cool.
Add nuts and carrots.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chunky chili
directions: In large heavy saucepan, heat oil.
Saute onions and garlic until soft, but not brown.
Add beef and sausage.
Cook until brown; pour off fat.
Add liquid from tomatoes.
Chop tomatoes and add to meat mixture with tomato paste, chili powder, cumin, oregano, baked beans, salt, sugar and cocoa powder.
Simmer partially covered for 2 hours, stirring often.
If too dry, add a little water as it cooks.
Stir in kidney beans and pinto beans. Cook 30 minutes longer or until meat is very tender.
Makes 16 servings.

title: mom's corn fritters
directions: Mix corn, flour, baking powder, salt and egg together.
Place juice from corn in measuring cup.
Add milk until measurement of mixture equals 1 cup.
Mix to first mixture; mix well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls in hot oil, until light brown on both sides. Remove from oil; dry on paper towels.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix all together; roll into little balls.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes; roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash head of cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Cook for five minutes in boiling water.
Drain well. Meanwhile, mix cream of chicken soup, shredded cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix with cauliflower in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until top bubbles.

title: oyster cracker tidbits
directions: Mix dressing in oil.
Add other ingredients.
Add to oyster crackers.
Spread in shallow baking pan and place in oven for 15 minutes at 200°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup water.
Cut cheese up in squares. Drain broccoli and place in bowl.
Mix in cheese.
Put 1/2 stick of butter in; stir.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crackers.
Pour remaining butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder; set aside.
Place eggs in another bowl; beat well, then add vanilla extract and fruit cocktail.
Fold fruit mixture into dry ingredients and mix well.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Combine these ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix ingredients in all 3 bowls together 30 minutes before serving.
(You might want to use less dressing, depending on the size of the cabbage you buy.)
Salad is still good the next day.

title: peruvian dish
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onions and meat.
When the meat browns, add vinegar, tomatoes and soy sauce.
Simmer until tender.
Serve over rice with French fries.

title: 10 pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients (except crusts).
Pour in pie crusts.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour or until tops brown slightly and crack.

title: cheese delight
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onions and bell pepper in 2 teaspoons margarine.
Cook macaroni and drain well.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Combine meat mixture with soups and tomatoes. Pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: squash soup
directions: Cook all except milk until soft.
Pour into a blender at high speed.
Add 1 cup of milk and return to heat.
Add the other cup when returned to heat.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Place cut up chicken wings in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chicken and marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, stirring every half hour.

title: banana-nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center. Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add egg mixture all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Add banana and nuts to mixture.
Stir well.
Batter should be lumpy.
Line muffin pan with paper cups.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans; serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: chet's burgers
directions: Form ground chuck into 4 patties; do not handle much. Sprinkle each side of the patty generously with the seasoning. Grill on high for 10 minutes, 5 minutes for each side.
Do not squish juice out of the hamburgers! Remove from grill and serve with remaining ingredients.

title: catfish with summer vegetables
directions: Slice zucchini in 1/2-inch thick rounds and cut bell pepper in thin strips.
Half mushrooms.
Put vegetables in 11 x 7-inch microwave safe baking dish.
Sprinkle with half the chives, salt and pepper.
Toss to mix.
Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes, stirring once until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Slice each tomato in 4 rounds.
Arrange fillets spoke fashion on top of vegetable mixture with thinnest parts toward center.
Put 2 slices tomato on each fillet, then sprinkle with remaining chives, salt and pepper.
Cover and microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn once until fish is opaque.
Serve with lemon.
Serve with crusty bread.
Yields 4 servings.

title: marshmallow-pineapple salad
directions: Boil eggs, sugar and juice together until thick, stirring constantly.
While hot, mix in cream cheese.
Then cool and add the pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill.

title: grace's pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and syrup.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Top with pecans.

title: "dumb cake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 13 x 9-inch cake pan and spread cherries over the bottom.
Spread pineapple over cherries. Sprinkle the cake mix evenly over all and top with bits of butter. Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes; cut
into squares and serve with whipped topping.

title: easy pineapple angel food cake
directions: Empty cake mix into large mixing bowl, add pineapple and juice. Mix with a spatula until all dry mix is moistened. Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake for 28-30 minutes at 350.

title: watermelon salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: waffles
directions: Add milk to beaten eggs. Sift dry ingredients together thoroughly, then add to liquid a little at a time. Add melted butter, beating thoroughly. Very light and fluffy waffles.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Combine the V-8 juice, tapioca and sugar.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Use a 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix well and bake at 225° to 250° for 5 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: spice tea
directions: Let tea stand 30 minutes.
Boil sugar and 1 quart water; add spices and let stand 30 minutes.
Mix tea to sugar water mixture; add juices and salt.
Add another 1/2 gallon water.

title: easy soup
directions: Put frozen vegetables in 2 quarts of boiling water.
Brown meat; drain.
Add to vegetables with rest of ingredients. Simmer until vegetables are tender and seasonings are well blended. Remove bay leaves.
Makes about 10 servings.
Serve with corn bread.
Freezes well or keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: chrusciki
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add shortening and mix as for pie dough.
Beat eggs, milk, sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla.
Make a well in middle of flour.
Pour egg mixture in well and mix together.
Dough should be soft.
If too hard, add more milk.
Let stand about 5 or 10 minutes.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in strips about 1 1/2 inches wide and 2 inches long.
Make slit in center and pull one end through. Heat about 4 inches oil in pan and deep fry Chrusciki on one side and turn over to fry other side.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: party shrimp
directions: In a large bowl combine everything except shrimp.
Place shrimp in boiling water and cook until pink (just done).
Drain and transfer to marinade.
Mix and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve using toothpicks.

title: six-layer dinner
directions: Place ingredients in order given in greased baking dish (8 x 12-inch).
Salt and pepper after each layer (optional).
Bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: chess cake or bobby cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.
Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and add sugars and vanilla; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour; blend well. (Stir in nuts, if desired.)
Pour in prepared pan and bake 40 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over top; let stand until cool.
Cut into squares.
This cake has a pudding-like consistency and will fall slightly after it is removed from oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Stir about every 15 minutes until last 1/2 hour.

title: oriental beef strips
directions: Combine wine, sugar, pepper, soy sauce, ginger and garlic in saucepan over low to medium heat.
Slice steak (across the grain) into 1/4 to 1/2-inch strips.
Place in container.
Pour hot marinade over strips, stir and seal.
Place in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes (up to 2 hours, depending on how much time you have).
Drain marinade off meat strips; save.
In a large preheated skillet, stir-fry strips over medium-high heat.
Add sliced vegetables after 2 to 3 minutes; stir-fry vegetables quickly.
Add cornstarch to marinade; stir well.
Pour marinade cornstarch mixture into skillet and bring up to a boil.
Reduce heat and check taste and consistency.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: goulash
directions: Mix together and place in casserole container or pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Use over rice or noodles.
Fast and delicious!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone. Cut chicken into pieces. Mix well with all ingredients, except corn flakes and butter. Put into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with corn flakes mixed with melted butter. Bake covered 1 hour at 350°.

title: gourmet tossed green salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Use dressing of your choice.

title: power bars
directions: In mixing bowl, beat butter and brown sugar.
Combine flour, oats and baking soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix on low speed until crumbly.
Press 2/3 mixture into jelly roll pan to form crust.

title: tiger milk candy
directions: Melt white chocolate in top of double boiler.
When melted, stir in peanut butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips; drizzle over top of candy.
Swirl with knife. Chill; cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add egg and banana mixture.
Beat in flour mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into loaf pan lined with 2 thicknesses of waxed paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: beef-cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into a ball.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Combine ingredients in bread machine according to manufacturer's instructions.
Process in dough cycle.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 to 5 times; divide in half.
Shape each portion into 9 rolls and place in an 8-inch round pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts for 40 minutes or until double in bulk.
Bake
at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: crunchy lemon squares
directions: Cream the shortening and gradually add sugar; blend until light.
Add egg yolks.
Mix in flour and grated lemon peel. Spread evenly on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Then spread with lemon meringue topping made by beating the egg whites until stiff and gradually adding the sugar and lemon juice.
Then add nuts and spread over the baked mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes; cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: tomatillo saucejust like ninfa's
directions: In a medium saucepan, simmer tomatillos, tomatoes, garlic and jalapeno for 15 minutes or until their liquid has evaporated.
This will thicken.
While the tomato mixture is simmering; place avacado in blender.
Spoon the thickened tomato mixture into the blender. Add sour cream, cilantro and salt.
Blend up to 5 minutes creating a smooth puree Taste and add salt if needed Serve with tostado chips or refrigerate for later use.
Can be frozen.
Doesn't turn gray like guacomole.
Makes 4 cups of dip.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Mix coconuts and nuts and spread in bottom of a 13 x 9 inch pan. Mix cake mix according to directions. Spread on top of coconut and nuts. Heat butter and cream cheese until soft enough to mix with confectioner sugar until smooth. Spread this on top of cake mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes. Because of sticky topping, cake must be served from pan.

title: corn bread
directions: Blend flour and corn meal along with baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add oil, plus beaten egg.
Stir in milk.
Stir briskly. Pour in sprayed 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, then brown top under broiler.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Add 1/2 stick of butter and cheese to hot broccoli; cheese should melt.
Melt remaining butter in skillet and add cracker crumbs.
Pour broccoli cheese mixture into baking dish; pour crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked goulash
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Combine with cooked macaroni and tomato sauce.
Spread grated cheese (as much as desired) on top of combination in large shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: mincemeat fruit cake
directions: To the mincemeat add raisins, nut meats, sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs, then beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together once, then sift and fold into the mincemeat mixture.
Bake in a well-greased tube cake pan in a slow oven (325°) for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil until reduced one-fourth.

title: bean soup canaan-style
directions: Soak beans in water; drain.
Add water to cover; add ham, celery, onion, carrots, pepper, garlic seasoning and catsup.
No salt needed as ham is salty.
Continue to cook for several hours, adding water and stirring when needed.
I cook on wood stove in cool weather. (Gale Ferris, Sr.'s recipe.)
Serve when tender and somewhat mushy.
Good with cornbread or crackers.

title: beef stew in pumpkin shell
directions: Saute beef with onion and garlic until browned.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, 2 teaspoons of salt, 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, sugar, white potatoes, sweet potatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add more salt, if desired, for taste.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, canned milk, cocoa and margarine for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla, oatmeal and nuts or raisins (if desired).

title: old virginia wassail
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot; bring to a boil.
Let boil for approximately 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Cover and let stand until cool.
Store in refrigerator. Serve hot, a good winter drink.

title: 12 hour crocked chili
directions: Stir meat and tomato paste together in crock-pot.
Stir in other ingredients (add no liquid).
Turn cooker on low heat. Cover and cook 12 hours.
Skim and discard any fat.
Makes 4 servings with 240 calories each.

title: layered casper salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Layer in large glass bowl:
lettuce, celery, cucumbers, eggs, peas, onions, bacon and tomatoes.
Spread topping on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread as directed.
Brown meat; add corn, meat and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour in 8-inch skillet with 2 tablespoon oil, melted.
Cook 40 minutes or until brown.
Let bread cool 5 minutes before slicing.

title: quick cobbler
directions: In a baking dish, place filling.
Cover with cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and beat at medium speed for 10 to 15 minutes, until well beaten and fluffy like whipped cream. Makes enough icing for 2 dozen cupcakes, one 9 x 13-inch cake or one 2 x 9-inch layer cake.

title: caramel-nut-crisps
directions: Melt caramels with water in saucepan, stirring over low heat until smooth.
Pour over combined cereals, coconut and nuts.
Toss until well coated.

title: myra's hot fudge cake
directions: Make cake in a long, square pan.
It needs to be thin layered so you can cut thin square slices (2 per person).
Place 1 slice or square on plate.
Add slice of ice cream.
Add other slice of cake, then pour 2 tablespoons of warm sauce over this.
Add whipped cream and a cherry.
This makes a quick dessert for Sunday lunch.
Kids love it because it looks like Shoney's hot fudge cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and form into a loaf. Spread remaining soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Slice meat to uniform size.
Mix all ingredients, except meat; mix well.
Pour over meat and marinate 24 hours.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread crumbs over butter. Add layers of chocolate chips, coconut and butterscotch chips. Pour milk over top layer.
Top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, beating constantly.

title: microwave nachos
directions: You will need a grater and microwave-safe platter.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Place bread cubes in a greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cubes.
Set baking dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.
Can be served plain or with a thin chocolate sauce.

title: zippy mustard pretzel dip
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in saucepan. Add egg and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Cook slightly.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Chill before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve with hard pretzels.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Use a 5-cup mold and chill 4 hours.

title: marshmallow frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture reaches soft ball stage, 230°. Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until mixture is of spreading consistency.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix beaten eggs, mayonnaise, cheese and soup together well. Stir in broccoli and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until thickened and a knife comes out clean when casserole is tested.

title: cocoa cookies
directions: Bring to boil 1 minute cocoa, milk, sugar and salt.
Add and dissolve peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Stir rapidly and drop on wax paper.
Coconut or nuts may be added.

title: geluski cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and parboil until tender.
Cut hard top if any off each leaf.
Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Make rolls out of mixture and roll them in leaves.
Put them in a big pan and cover with V-8 juice.
If that doesn't cover it, put in some more. Bake in 350° oven 4 to 5 hours or 250° oven for 8 to 9 hours.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: In covered jar or shaker, combine ingredients.
Chill.
Shake well before using.
Serve on salad greens.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan overnight. Cut into squares.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan or 2 round pans.
Beat all ingredients on low speed, scraping bowl constantly 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Bake in rectangular pan 40 to 50 minutes, or round pans 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 15 servings, 310 calories per serving.

title: angel food
directions: Sift 1 cup of the sugar 2 or 3 times.
Then sift flour with the other 1/2 cup sugar 3 or 4 times.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla and salt until whites stand in peaks.
Beat in the 1 cup of sugar.
Fold in the flour and sugar mixture until well blended.
Bake in tube pan or 12-inch square cake pan at 350° until top is brown and cake springs back when touched.
Make sure pan is washed well and no grease particles remain from previous use.

title: french bread pudding
directions: Soak French bread in homogenized milk until soft.
Add slightly beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla, pie spice, apples, raisins and butter and mix well.
Mix in balance of milk and bake at 375° for 60 minutes or until brown.

title: creamy lobster soup
directions: Heat butter.
When hot, add onion.
Cover and cook 2 minutes over medium heat.
Add potatoes and season well.
Pour in cream and milk; season again.
Bring to boil and cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add mushrooms and continue cooking.
Stir in lobster and simmer 3 to 4 minutes over low heat.
Sprinkle with chives and paprika before serving.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Peel and cut squash into small pieces.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in squash until well coated.
Place in greased baking dish and cover with milk.
Bake at 350° until squash is done, approximately 45 minutes.

title: cake of pleasure
directions: Place sugar and pineapple in a pan; simmer for 10 minutes. Remove from heat and cool until cake is baked as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove cake from oven.
Punch holes all over cake. Spread pineapple over cake and let soak in.
Mix pudding as directed.
Spread over cake.
Put coconut all over top of cake, then cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate. It is better the second day.

title: oven baked caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped popcorn in large shallow pans. Put in slow oven at 250° to keep warm and crisp. Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Place on medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Continue to cook to 248° (about 5 minutes). Remove from heat and stir in baking soda. Syrup will foam.

title: christy's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate. Before serving, add 2 sliced bananas, if desired.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix cake mix, melted margarine and 3/4 cup nuts.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar and 6 tablespoons nuts.
Put on preceeding mixture.
Sprinkle 6 tablespoons nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Mix all ingredients, except crust.
Place crust in pie pan.
Pour ingredients in pie pan and cover with remaining crust.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is light brown and flaky.

title: no crust cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and salt.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla.
Bak at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add package of taco seasoning. Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Layer each ingredient:
Spread crescent roll dough in bottom of dish.
Spread cooked ground beef on top.
Spread on can of refried beans.
Pour on jar of picante sauce.
Spread on sour cream.
Sprinkle on black olives.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Sprinkle crushed nacho chips on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Pour in muffin papers in muffin pan and freeze.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in pumpkin and water.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Spoon into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: creamy vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with tight fitting lid. Shake thoroughly to blend.
Chill.
Makes 1 cup.

title: hot chocolate mix(great christmas gift)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in gallon jar.
To serve, fill cup 1/2 full with chocolate.
Mix and add boiling water.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 2 1/2 to 3 quart saucepan, over low heat, melt margarine. Remove from heat. Add flour, sugar, coca, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla. Stir with a spoon until well blended. Stir in 1 1/2 c. chocolate chips. Spread in greased 9 X 13 pan. Sprinkle with remaining chips. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix Oreos and margarine in bowl and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Gently stir in 1 1/4 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Pour 3 1/4 cup milk in large bowl, add pudding mix. Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Let stand 5 minutes until thickened.
Drop remaining Cool Whip and spread to cover pudding layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: low-fat cheese cake
directions: Combine Yogurt Cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Mix gently until well blended.
Pour into prepared crust and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool slightly and refrigerate, uncovered, 24 hours.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in iron skillet.
Beat egg and add milk. Add corn meal,
flour
and salt; mix well.
Add melted butter; mix well.
Pour into skillet.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: beer muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Grease muffin pans and bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 or more.

title: pickles
directions: Fill quart jars with small cucumbers (pickling size).
Add 3 cloves of garlic, one on bottom and two on top, to each jar. Place sprig of fresh dill in each jar.
Boil water, vinegar and salt solution for 5 minutes.
Pour over cucumbers in jars.
Seal with lids and rings.
Let stand for 4 to 6 weeks.

title: bateta nu shaak
directions: Get oil to smoking point in thick bottomed vessel.
Put in mustard seed.
Will start crackling.
Put in onions and garlic and saute for 1 minute.
Put potatoes into sauteed garlic and onions with salt, sugar and paprika.
Cook on slow fire until potatoes are cooked, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: double chocolate sugar-free pie
directions: Combine pie filling and milk; whip until mixed well.
Add 1 cup of Cool Whip whipped topping; mix well.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Spread 2 cups of Cool Whip on top.
Cover; chill for 3 hours.
Serve.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna and mix all ingredients.
Serve on bread or with crackers.

title: kim's foolproof cheesecake
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Pack into the bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese with sugar, then beat in eggs (one at a time).
Fold in the sour cream and vanilla.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then shut oven off and leave it in the oven for at least 1 hour (or overnight).

title: cranberry mold
directions: Mix cooled gelatin with cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Fold in sour cream combined with mayonnaise.
Pour into oiled mold and refrigerate until firm.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: In a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise, anchovies, parsley, chives, green onions, vinegar and tarragon until well mixed. Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on tossed greens, chilled vegetables or cold seafood or poultry.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Make sauce by combining soup, cheese, green chilies and milk in top of double boiler.
Brown meat and add onion, garlic salt, salt and pepper. Dip tortillas in hot oil and drain.
Roll meat in tortillas and place in baking dish.
Cover with cheese sauce and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can add grated cheese.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Dressing:
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Let stand while preparing salad.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Boil until crackle stage when dropped in cold water (about 10 minutes).
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff.
When syrup is cooked, set off burner until it quits bubbling.
Pour gradually into egg whites.
Add vanilla and beat until it holds its shape.
Add nuts.

title: *snowball cake
directions: Soften plain gelatin in cold water.
Pour boiling water over red jello and dissolve.
Combine with plain gelatin.
Add sugar, crushed pineapple, cut up cherries, coconut and lemon juice.
Put in refrigerator to chill, but not jell.
Prepare Dream Whip as package directs and add to gelatin mixture.
Tear the cake into small pieces and put into deep dish or oblong cake pan.
Cover with gelatin mixture and place in refrigerator until jelled.

title: margarita jello jiggler shooter
directions: Mix Jell-O, tequila, Margarita mix with the boiling water and stir until dissolved in a 9 x 9 pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill for four hours.
After chilled, cut into cubes.
Use fingers to eat and eat with caution.
Substitute cherry Jell-O and 6 ounces of rum for the alcohol and mix.
Or try sugar-free Jell-O also.

title: neverlasting cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Thoroughly mix oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla
by
hand.	Add
pineapple and juice.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well.
Blend in bananas.
Grease and flour a Bundt
pan and add batter.	Bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: adaline kohn's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, applesauce and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Sift together and add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Beat well.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Bake in oblong pan or cupcakes at 350° for about 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cajun beignets
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add milk and egg and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat (oil) heated to 375°.
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with syrup and butter.

title: seven times one chile and beans
directions: Dry-fry meat in nonstick frypan until crumbled and brown.
Add chopped onion and peppers; saute until clear.
Chop tomatoes in blender (do not puree) to break into small chunks.
Mix all ingredients into crock-pot and cook for several hours at low heat. The longer you cook it, the better.
(Low-fat.)

title: denise's easy cheesecake
directions: Mix Ricotta Cheese, Eggs and sugar in a bowl.
Prepare cake mix as per directions on box.
Pour cake batter into cake pan, then spread Cheese mixture over the batter.
Bake at 375 degrees for approximately 1 hour.

title: lisa's pineapple cake
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, sugar, baking soda,
eggs and pineapple together.
Bake in a 9 inch x 13 inch pan for 30 - 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into pie shell and freeze.

title: bourbon roll
directions: Mix milk and bourbon; add to crumbs.
Mix well.
Add fruit and pecans; work with hands until all crumbs are mixed.
Divide into 3 rolls.
Sift powdered sugar on waxed paper.
Roll and shape with fingers.
Cover with powdered sugar.
Store in refrigerator. Slice to serve.
Freezes well.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone.
Spray Pam in bottom of casserole dish and spread chicken over bottom.
Combine soup and broth together and heat thoroughly.
Pour mixture over chicken.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Hollow out bread and fill with dip.
Tear bread into pieces and dip into spinach dip.

title: stuffed baked mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, Parmesan, bacon bits and garlic. Spoon about 1 tablespoon of the mixture into each mushroom cap and sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese on top. Place mushroom caps in a baking dish and bake until cheese is melted. Serve hot!

title: cinnamon snails
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Spray a baking sheet with nonstick coating spray.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle sugar mixture on rolling surface.
Unroll 1 breadstick.
Coil tightly. Wrap another breadstick around coil, forming a larger coil.
Place on sugared surface.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place sugared side up on baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining 6 bread sticks. Bake in the 375° oven about 15 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: onion nuggets
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Add onion salt, mustard and red pepper.
Chill for half an hour.
Form into balls the size of a walnut and roll in crumbled onions.
Place on pick for serving.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach several times.
Dry thoroughly.
Tear into bite-size pieces; remove stems.
Wash and slice tomatoes.
Combine spinach, mushrooms and bacon in a bowl.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Pour on Caesar dressing and toss.
Garnish with eggs.
Total fat grams:
33.9; per serving, 5.7.

title: hobo dinner for two
directions: Make 2 large patties from the ground chuck and season to taste.
Slice the potatoes, carrot and onion like little wheels. Cut bell pepper into strips.
Tear off aluminum foil large enough to place the ingredients in the middle and fold over in the following order:
potatoes, beef patties, onion, carrot and bell pepper strips.
Top with 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and sprinkle with seasonings.
Pull up foil and fold over top.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cook for 1 1/2 hours at 450°.
May be cooked for 3 hours at 350°.
Great to cook while at church.

title: japanese hamburger
directions: Saute almonds in butter until lightly browned.
Set aside. Brown beef well, leaving
in chunks.
Stir in water and bring to boil.
Stir in noodles.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Bring to full boil over medium heat, separating vegetables and stirring frequently.
Cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce and sprinkle with almonds.

title: egg noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain off water.
Cook beef and onion and drain off fat.
In large casserole dish put meat, onion, noodles, cream cheese, corn and soup with 1/2 glass milk or water.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Serve with a salad.

title: cottage cheese danish
directions: Break up bread in a bowl.
Mix first 3 ingredients in a cup and spoon over bread.
Microwave until cottage cheese begins to bubble.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package. Cook rice. Heat undiluted soup and Cheez Whiz and let melt. Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish. Cover with breadcrumbs or crushed Ritz crackers and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour; put over pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese over pineapple mixture.
Next layer the cracker crumbs.
Pour the melted butter over the cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Good with ham or chicken.

title: mild-cajun cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375° to 400°.
Mix cornbread mix, Bisquick, egg and milk. Fry and drain well the breakfast sausage.
Cool, then add to cornbread mixture. Stir in grated cheese, corn, onion and bell pepper.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake for about 45 minutes.
Will be crisp.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Add sugar and flour to sour cream.
Mix peaches into cream mixture.
Pour into crust and place pastry strips over filling.
tags: pastry strips made from another pie shell

title: poulet maman
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking, turning once until golden, about 10 minutes.

title: things
directions: Cut Spam into 3 pieces per can.
Cut cheese into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Peel onions and cut in halves.
Hand grind Spam, cheese and onions.
Alternate to clean grinder.
Mix all together.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Wrap buns in foil.
