Place on cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese melts.

title: hot dogs in barbecue sauce
directions: Mix onion, pepper and tomato juice in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to boil.
Add vinegar, catsup, butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until butter is melted.
Add salt and sugar.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, or until thickened.
Add hot dogs and cook 8 to 10 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef and onions in skillet and drain.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape loaf.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: light as a feather donuts
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Set aside to cool.
Take warm water (tepid); add yeast.
Stir until melted. Take cooled milk mixture and add about 1/3 of flour and all of the yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour to make dough.
Work dough and let rise until double in size. Then work dough again and cut donuts out on wax paper and let rise again.
Put shortening or oil in pan, deep enough for donuts to float.
Turn and dip in glaze of powdered sugar, vanilla and milk to make a thin glaze.
Set aside to cool.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Use 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes. Poke holes through cake with fork. Combine milk, flour, sugar and 1/2 cup of the coconut in saucepan. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 minute. Carefully spoon over warm cake. Allow liquid to soak down through holes. Cool completely. Fold 1/2 cup of coconut into topping and spread over cake. Sprinkle with remaining coconut. Chill overnight. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: rump roast or italian roast beef sandwich
directions: Mix salt and ginger together and rub all over roast.
Brown roast on top of stove in roaster or Dutch oven in about 4 tablespoons oil or fat.
After roast browns, turn heat down to medium-low.
Add water, bay leaves, whole cloves and diced onions. After roast starts cooking, reduce heat and simmer until roast is done, approximately 3 1/2 hours.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Heat water, margarine, Mazola oil and cocoa to boiling and pour over flour and sugar (sifted together in a bowl).
Add buttermilk with soda added, eggs and vanilla.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Pour milk in a deep, narrow bottom mixing bowl.
Add Dream Whip and pudding; beat at low speed until well blended.
Gradually increase speed to high and whip until mixture forms soft peaks, 4 to 6 minutes.
Makes 3 cups.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, put 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in next 3 ingredients. Spoon into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar; continue beating until stiff peaks.
Spread over filling.
Bake until brown.

title: lemon-butter sauce
directions: In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in real lemon juice and salt.
Serve with seafood, fish or vegetables.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil the coffee, water, vanilla and sugar to dissolve.
Let cool. Add vodka.
Pour in jars and let set 1 month in refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fiesta cheesecake
directions: Combine tortilla chips and butter; press onto bottom of lightly greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla, mix well.
Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder all together then add oatmeal and nuts.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator to chill 2 hours or overnight (up to 2 weeks).
Roll in balls, then powdered sugar.
Put on cookie sheet and press down with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: fried cabbage supreme
directions: Fry bacon in a large pan.
Add onion, garlic, potatoes and cabbage.
Simmer until light brown.
Pour in chicken broth.
Add salt, pepper and seeds.
Cover and simmer until brown.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well. Blend in melted butter.
(Blend cocoa in melted butter before adding to egg mixture.)
Before adding flour, mix flour, salt and baking powder together, then add to egg mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from sides.
Cool in pan.

title: spinach and artichoke casserole
directions: Drain the artichokes.
Quarter and place on bottom of a 3-quart casserole.
Squeeze as much moisture as possible from the spinach and layer it on top of the artichokes.
With an electric mixer, blend the cream cheese, mayonnaise and butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in the milk.
Spread this mixture over the top of the spinach.
Sprinkle with pepper and the cheese.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 minutes or until the top is lightly browned.
(I have baked it in Pyrex pan, and it took about 25 minutes.)

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add everything, except beans.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans; mix well.
Pour into baking dish; top with corn bread batter spooned evenly over the top in a thin layer. Bake in hot oven until browned.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Add chicken wings. Soak chicken in batter overnight and deep fry.
Dip in flour just before frying.
Serves 4.

title: beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients into 6-quart Dutch oven; stir to blend. Cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours. Stir occasionally. (Freezes well.)

title: chicken breasts dianne
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper or plastic wrap; pound slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a microwave dish, melt butter and mix with oil.
Place chicken breasts in dish, coating breasts on both sides.
Microwave at High power for 3 minutes; let rest for 1 minute.
Turn breasts over.

title: spanish custard
directions: Boil sugar in a little water to caramelize in the pan to be used to bake custard.
Set aside to cool.
Empty condensed milk into large mixing bowl.
With electric mixer, beat milk for 30 seconds.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beating 30 seconds after each addition.
Fill empty cans with milk and vanilla.
Pour milk slowly into mixture and blend well.
Transfer to caramelized pan. Place in a shallow pan of hot water and bake 45 minutes at 400° or 1 hour at 350°.
If top browns too quickly, cover with foil.

title: old fashion apple dumplings
directions: Pare and core apples; leave whole.
To make pastry, sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening until particles are about the size of small lima beans.
Sprinkle milk over mixture and press together and lightly, working dough only enough to hold together.
Roll dough as for pastry and cut in 6 squares; place an apple on each.
Fill cavity in apple with sugar and cinnamon.
Pat dough around apple to cover completely.
Fasten edges securely on top of apple.
Place dumplings 1 inch apart in a greased baking pan.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wooden bowl works best to mix ingredients.
Mash garlic in bowl with fork.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add oil, 1/2 cup for medium salad.
Add Parmesan cheese unti thickens somewhat. Cut tomatoes and onions in slices and add to mixture.
Dry the lettuce.
Break in pieces and mix into oil/cheese mixture.
Add salami, cheese and carrots.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Mix catsup, sugar, water and soy sauce.
Cut chestnuts in half and roll raw bacon around cut chestnuts.
Pin with toothpicks. Place in baking dish and cover with sugar, catsup
mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven 45 minutes to one hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish.
Pour both cans of corn, including liquid, into casserole dish.
Stir in eggs. Add enough crackers to thicken.
Bake 20 minutes, uncovered. Cover top with shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese bubbles and starts to brown.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cube and melt Velveeta cheese in microwave.
When melted, stir sausage and tomatoes into cheese.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into greased mold and freeze.

title: tamale beef pie
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce, chili powder, sugar, salt and garlic.
Cook on low for 30 minutes, stir occasionally.
Stir in cheese and olives and put in a round 2-1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and shortening.
Pour over hot meat mixture.
Bake in preheated oven 15 to 20 minutes until top is golden brown.
Bake at 425 °. Serves 6.

title: chew bread
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar; stir well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add other ingredients, stirring with spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: tomato flower salad
directions: Cut stems from tomatoes.
Cut each tomato into 8 wedges, leaving wedges attached at bottom.
Fan wedges slightly; set aside. Combine cottage cheese and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Spoon evenly into tomato flowers.
Serve immediately.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with the vanilla wafers.
Cut strawberries up and mix with strawberry glaze.
Pour strawberry mixture over vanilla wafers.
Just before serving, spread thawed Cool Whip over top.

title: fried rice with pork and water chestnuts
directions: Heat peanut oil and sesame oil in wok over medium heat.
Add garlic and ginger (do not brown).
Add rice and fry over high heat until rice begins to change color.
Sprinkle with soy sauce and continue frying.
Add ham and water chestnuts and stir well.
Move rice to sides and egg in middle.
Stir until almost dry.
Mix with rice and add green onions.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: bohemian style turnips(diet)
directions: Saute onion in butter in a skillet until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and 1 cup water.
Cook until tender and liquid is dissolved.
Serve at once.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar and syrup to hard crack stage.
Add soda and stir briskly; pour into buttered pan but don't spread.
Put in cool place until hard; break into pieces.
Store in tightly covered tin.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease iron skillet.
(You can use large glass baking dish.)
Mix ingredients and pour in pan.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy raspberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Melt frozen raspberries in jello and mix well.
Add applesauce and mix.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.

title: melissa's favorite butterscotch raisin cookies(jumbo recipe; makes 6 to 8 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream first 4 ingredients, then add remaining.
Drop golf ball size cookies on baking sheets sprayed with baking spray 3 inches apart (1 dozen per tray).
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool even if they look uncooked when you're pulling them out of the oven.
They harden when they cool and are easy to overbake.
Cook and store in airtight container.

title: grammy's cookie bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips, stirring by hand.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Pour mixture into oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is light brown.
Allow to cool; cut into bars.

title: gumdrop bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom only of a loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Beat all of the ingredients, except the gumdrops and the nuts, in a large mixing bowl on low speed for 15 seconds. Then beat on medium speed constantly for 30 seconds.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.

title: easy ham and cheese bake
directions: Spread margarine in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, mix bread cubes, ham, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese.
Spread in dish. In large bowl, mix eggs and milk together well, season with salt and pepper.
Pour over bread cubes mixture and cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake, uncovered, for 32 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Up oven temperature to 350°.
Add remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Return to oven and bake 10 to 20 minutes longer, or until firm to the touch and golden brown.
Sprinkle with green onions, cut into squares and serve. Makes 12 servings.

title: asparagus with cheese sauce
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus. Remove scales with vegetable peeler, if desired. Arrange asparagus in a steamer basket over boiling water; cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: midget meat loaf
directions: Mix and pack in muffin pans.
Cover with the other half of the tomato paste.
Bake at 425 ° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Can be topped with grated cheese.)

title: no-bake fresh peach cobbler
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, salt and water.
Stir to dissolve, then cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add remaining sugar and butter, return to heat and cook until sugar dissolves.
Add vanilla and peaches.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into 8-inch square pan or individual serving dishes.
Top with granola or gingersnaps.
Serve with cream, whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 6 to 8.

title: tomato sauce
directions: In a large frying pan, heat olive oil.
Add onion and cook until soft but not brown.
Add garlic, tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir and cook, covered, until tomatoes are soft, about 30 minutes.
Add basil or parsley and cook another 5 minutes.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Place one vanilla wafer in each liner, if using cupcake size. Split wafer, if using mini cupcake size.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar.
Spoon over wafers.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Top with choice of fruit, preserves, nuts or chocolate.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain. mix beef mixture, soup, rotel, seasoning, milk and worcestershire sauce together. Put cheese in tortilla shells and roll; place in buttered 9x13 casserole pan. Pour beef mixture over, pour extra cheese on top. Bake 350° for 30 min. Top with lettuce, tomato, black olives and sour cream.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and cut into round circles.
Place in 2 or 3-quart deep pan and add milk and water.
Cut Velveeta into large chunks and place about half inside of potatoes.
Add margarine and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
About 10 minutes before done, add rest of cheese.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: "sausage and mushroom calzone"
directions: Cook sausage and mushrooms in large skillet until no longer pink; drain. Stir in 1/2 can of pizza sauce. Roll dough on lightly floured surface to 12-inch circle. Place on greased cookie or pizza sheet. Spoon sausage mixture over half the dough to within 1/2-inch of edge. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Moisten edges of dough with water. Fold dough in half over filling. Seal by pressing with tines of fork. Cut slits in top of calzone. Brush with water. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until golden. Heat remaining pizza sauce and serve with calzone. (Add hot sauce if desired -- IT'S SO GOOD!!!)

title: chewy pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, egg, crackers and catsup together.
Add onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder; mix well.
Add shredded cheese; mix well. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour in rectangle pan (make mixture into 2 small loaves).
Put some catsup on top before baking and spread to cover top (about 2 tablespoons per loaf).

title: lasagne
directions: Mix meat and sauce together.
Add small amount to bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place layer of noodles in pan; cover with sauce and sprinkle with cheese of any kind.
Keep adding noodles, sauce and cheese until all ingredients are used and ending with cheese on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat meat strips with flour, brown in butter or margarine. Push to one side of pan.
Saute onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Stir mixture together, cover pan and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine mushroom juice, sour cream, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Pour over meat.
Simmer about 30 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and brown, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Layer on serving plate the softened cream cheese.
Cover with cocktail sauce, then chopped onions.
Add drained and rinsed shrimp and top with cheese.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: sausage dish
directions: In bowl, mix cubed potatoes, onion slices and pepper slices. Add the Wesson oil and mix.
Add sausage pieces; mix again.
Place ingredients flat in pan; cook for 1 hour at 350°, stirring occasionally during cooking.

title: marinated vegetables(lo-fat)
directions: Drain and rinse canned vegetables.
Boil sugar, vinegar, oil and water.
Pour over vegetables while hot.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: sandy's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and 3/4 cup milk; heat.
When mixture boils, add remaining milk.
Boil 10 minutes (no less).
After taking off stove, add vanilla, then beat, scraping sides often. Pour into well buttered dish.
Cut after 5 minutes, before it cools.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Beat eggs with sugar for 2 minutes, gradually add oil and beat 2 minutes.
Add extract alternately.
Fold flour mixture and zucchini until moistened.
Stir in pecans and raisins; do not overmix.
Pour batter into well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack; wrap in plastic wrap.

title: strawberry cream
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries, saving juice.
Add pineapple (save juice) and sliced bananas.
Combine juices saved from fruit with water to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid. Stir together and pour 1/2 of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex or non-metallic dish.
Chill 1 hour; spread sour cream on top. Pour rest of Jell-O mixture on top of sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: texas beans
directions: Combine ingredients in a large baking dish.
Top with bacon strips and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: texas taters
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into a sprayed or greased baking dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not stir while cooking.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine and melt together the first five ingredients on low heat.
Bring to a boil, then put on medium heat and cook to soft ball temperature on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper immediately.

title: cornwallis yams
directions: Cook potatoes and mash. Add all other ingredients, except marshmallows; blend. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Melt butter and saute almonds until light brown.
Stir in soup with flour and milk.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly until thick, approximately 5 minutes.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer 1/2 cup potatoes, chicken, carrots, plus 1/2 of sauce.
Repeat layers and top with remaining sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugar well.
Add flour and mix.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Press into an ungreased pan (10 x 15-inch, jelly roll size).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20
minutes. Cut into squares and leave in pan until cool.

title: rainbow salad
directions: One at a time, dissolve each Jell-O into 1 1/2 cups hot water. Put Knox gelatine in hot water and set aside.
Bring to boil the milk and sugar.
Stir constantly.
Add Knox gelatine and sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Divide into 3 bowls; set aside.

title: czechoslovakian cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg yolks and extract.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Spoon half of batter into lightly greased 7 x 11-inch pan or 8-inch square pan.
Spread evenly with damp fingers.
Spread jam on top of batter within 1/4 inch of edges.
Best way to do this is to flatten the batter by hand and fit in pan.
Bake 1 hour or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack; cut into small bars and sprinkle with 10x sugar when cooled.
Makes 32 to 36 cookies.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bring to a boil 2 sticks of butter, 1 cup water and 6 tablespoons cocoa.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 2 cups sugar and baking soda.
Beat in eggs and sour cream.
Pour mixture into a greased and lightly floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 22 minutes.

title: microwave apples
directions: Slice apples.
Put in a microwaveproof dish.
The best apples to use for microwave are white apples.
Dot apples with butter and approximately 1 cup sugar.
Cover with plastic wrap leaving a small opening.
Microwave approximately 13 minutes.

title: peach dessert
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows. Refrigerate over night.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Cook in a 375° oven for 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: holy chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Cut in small pieces and put in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch buttered baking dish.
Combine soups, sour cream and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and sprinkle crumbs over the soup and cream mixture. Spread the melted butter over the crackers.
Cook until bubbly and hot through in 350° oven.

title: crispy sweets(3 days at least)
directions: Drain all the liquid from pickles.
Replace liquid with vinegar and sugar.
Place in refrigerator.
Two times a day, shake the jar so that the sugar mixes with the pickles.
Make sure you have the lid very tight so that jar can be put upside down every other time you shake the jar.
Pickles are ready when all the sugar is dissolved.
A delicious treat.

title: cookies from a cake mix
directions: You can add raisins, nuts and coconut.

title: black bean dip
directions: In a blender or food processor, combine beans, 1 tablespoon chopped onions, vinegar, orange juice and garlic.
Blend until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Ready to serve.
Garnish with remaining 1 tablespoon red onions.
Serve with tortilla chips, raw veggies or toasted pita triangles.

title: ginger peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ginger ale.
Chill. Fold in and add peaches.
Chill 3 hours.
You may want to double the recipe.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop one teaspoon at a time of mixture into deep fryer cooker. Cook until golden brown.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: molasses squares
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Sift together and add to creamed mixture the rest of ingredients.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and sprinkle top with granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into squares.

title: memorial cheesecake
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and set aside to cool.
Mix sugar and cream cheese and whip.
Add Jell-O and fold in Cool Whip. Pour in crust (graham or the 3 layer dessert crust).
Refrigerate.

title: country style green beans
directions: Empty green beans into a pot (do not drain). Add diced onion. Bring to a boil. While the green beans are simmering, fry out bacon; let drain. Mix together vinegar and sugar; add this mixture to bacon grease. Bring to boil. Turn off green beans. Pour off half of liquid from the beans. Place in serving dish. Add bacon grease mixture to beans; stir and crumble bacon on top. Enjoy!

title: sharp cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in water.

title: sweet potato souffle'roswell, new mexico
directions: Combine and place in 2 qt. baking dish.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and eggs and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cheese, sugar and eggs and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: very garlic bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spread thinly onto each slice of bread. Wrap in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: special chicken salad
directions: Place chicken cubes in 1-quart microwave-safe casserole. Cover with casserole lid.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes or until chicken is tender, stirring once. Drain and cool.
Drain pineapple juice into 2-cup glass measure. Blend in sugar and cornstarch.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring once.
Cool and refrigerate. Combine chicken, pineapple, grapes, water chestnuts and celery in 6-cup serving dish; mix lightly.
Blend yogurt into pineapple juice mixture.
Pour over salad.
Mix lightly to coat. Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes about 5 servings containing 255 calories each.

title: apple bavarian cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly saute the almonds in margarine. Blot on paper towel.
Set aside.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; add garlic, parsley flakes, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer until thick, about a hour. Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles and drain.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, dissolving bouillon cubes in boiling water before adding rice.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend powdered sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: buns
directions: Combine cream, salt, butter and flavoring.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Stir yeast into lukewarm water and sugar. When cream mixture is cool, add yeast mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Do not knead.
Stir with spoon.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Spoon into muffin pans, 1/2 full.
Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, beating until fluffy. Mix a paste of cocoa and vinegar; add to margarine mixture.
Sift salt, soda and flour together; add to mixture.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and coloring.
Mix and pour into greased or paper-lined pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oreo cheesecake
directions: Mix together Oreo crumbs and melted butter.
Press into buttered
9-inch
spring-form pan.	Refrigerate until ready to use.
Beat together cream cheese, brown sugar, eggs plus yolks and vanilla
until
smooth and creamy.
Pour half into crust. Layer with
broken
up
Oreo
cookies.
Cover
with remaining mixture. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes;
lower heat to 225° for 50 minutes. Turn
off oven for 30 minutes.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.

title: sour cream pound cake(crusty top)
directions: Sift flour with soda; set aside.
Cream butter and add sugar slowly, beating constantly to cream well.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour, beating well. Stir in vanilla and pour into sprayed 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grilled herb-mustard chicken
directions: Marinate chicken 4 hours or overnight.
Drain and save marinade to baste over chicken while grilling.
Place on lightly greased grill skin side up.
Turn frequently while basting with marinade until done, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: working mom's steak
directions: Place steaks in bottom of crock-pot.
Pour on Chicken Tonight sauce.
Turn crock-pot on low and let cook 8 to 10 hours.
Make a potato and vegetable and supper is ready!

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Brown ground beef; salt and pepper to taste.
Drain ground beef.
Add pork and beans, honey mustard, jelly and ketchup.
When mixture begins to bubble, reduce heat and let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed grape leaves(arabic-syrian)
directions: *Grape Leaves:
If packed in salt water, rinse and drain.
If using fresh leaves, wash thoroughly and cover with hot water until limp.
Drain and set aside.

title: low-fat ham spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix until well blended.
Cover and chill.

title: ma springer's chow-chow
directions: I cut way down on the peppers.

title: banana bisque with cinnamon toast croutons
directions: In baking pan, toss bread with butter. Arrange in one layer and bake in preheated 400° oven, tossing occasionally, for 3 minutes.
In small bowl combine sugar, cinnamon and a pinch of salt.
Toss croutons to coat them and bake in oven for 5 minutes, tossing occasionally until crisp and brown.
Let cool.

title: joni's cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar; beat in egg, syrup and vanilla.
Add flour; stir in oats and coconut.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend pudding mix in the crushed pineapple (juice too).
Then add Cool Whip and the marshmallows.
Chopped nuts can be added if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter or oleo until soft.
Stir in soup.
Heat about 2 minutes.
Add rice and beans with dry mustard and Tabasco. Mix and season to taste.
Add diced meat.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: weezie's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with bacon strips.
Mix soup with water.
Salt and pepper chicken and place on top of bacon.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle garlic, salt and pepper over casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cook rice separately and serve with chicken and the delicious gravy it makes.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Put all together in large pan.
Heat slowly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: gazpacho
directions: In
blender, combine 1 tomato, 1/4 onion, 1/4 cucumber, 1/4 green
pepper,
pimento
and 1/2 cup tomato juice.	Blend covered at high speed for 30 seconds to puree the vegetables. In
a
large bowl, mix pureed vegetables with remaining tomato juice,
cup oil, the vinegar, hot pepper seasoning, salt and	pepper. Refrigerate
until	well
chilled
hours). Meanwhile,
use garlic
and
remaining
oil to saute croutons until
brown;
set aside.
Chop remaining vegetables and place in separate bowls. Serve as accompaniment with chilled soup.

title: fried salmon patties
directions: Empty salmon into mixing bowl after pouring off approximately 3/4 of fluid (debone salmon as much as possible).
Add egg, celery, onion and crushed crackers.
Mix thoroughly and make into 4 patties.
Heat approximately 1/4-inch cooking oil in medium size frying pan.
Cook patties until brown on one side (about 2 minutes) and turn over, browning patties on either side.
Place patties on paper towels to drain oil.
Serve hot.

title: pineapple cottage salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Drain pineapple; dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add juice from pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy; fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Add
dry
ingredients
alternately to shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add	sour
cream
towards the end.
Let stand overnight to chill.
Roll
out and cut out.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Frost and decorate.
Great Christmas cookies.

title: garlic and onion bread
directions: Spread on bread.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes wrapped in tinfoil.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add salt, sugar, lemon juice and rind.
Chill until almost set.
Whip chilled milk.
Add lemon jello mixture (beat well lightly).
Grease bottom of baking dish with margarine.
Pack 1/2 of crumbs in dish.
Add mixture; put rest of crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: dilly squash
directions: Slice squash crosswise 1/4-inch thick.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add squash, parsley, dill weed, salt and onion powder. Cover and cook over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve piping hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Combine Bananas, Sugar, Butter, Egg and Vanilla in a mixing bowl, mix well.
Mix in Flour, Baking Soda and pinch of Salt.
Pour into greased cupcake pan and bake at 325 for 25 minutes.

title: corn sticks
directions: Sift together the corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients, mix well and pour into hot, greased corn stick pans.
Bake in 475° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: velma's cafe house dressing
directions: Put in food processor and mix well.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute margarine and onion.
Blend sauteed onion, broccoli with liquid in blender.
Pour mixture in large pot and simmer with rest of ingredients.
Stir frequently until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: broccoli casserole(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 2-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: In buttered casserole dish, put 1 package crushed Doritos, then deboned chicken.
In saucepan add soups, tomatoes and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken and top with other package of Doritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbling.

title: cold tomato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sour cream.
Chill until very cold.
An hour before serving, mix in sour cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Broccoli may be used instead of the squash.

title: make shift lomi-lomi salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients and let sit in refrigerator one hour before serving.

title: butter finger cake
directions: Go by directions on box and cook cake. When done let cake cool. Cut cake in half. Crumble up 1/2 in bottom of long cake pan. Mix powdered sugar, cool whip, oleo with mixer. Put half on top of cake and cut up one candy bar on top of that. Crumble the rest of cake and put on top of cool whip. Pour the rest of cool whip mixture and cut up the other 2 candy bars. Keep cool.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a 15 x 9-inch Pyrex dish. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese the last 15 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Bring water to boil; add salt, pepper and spices.
Turn down to a slow boil.
Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken out of broth; bone chicken and lay aside.

title: super nachos
directions: Cook beef and sausage; drain.
Add onion, hot sauce and green chilies.
Spread beans in an ovenproof pan; top with meat mixture. Cover with cheese.
Drizzle taco sauce over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together and set aside the cake flour and salt.
Work shortening with a spoon until soft. Gradually add, while beating, the sugar.
Beat until light.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Set aside. Combine red food coloring and cocoa.
Mix until smooth.
Add to shortening mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Combine and mix well, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to shortening and cocoa mixture alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth after each addition.
Combine and blend well.
Fold vinegar and baking soda into batter.
Spoon into 2 greased 9-inch layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; cool to lukewarm. Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup warm water and add to mixture along with egg and 2 1/2 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add 2 3/4 cups flour and stir to make a soft dough. Turn onto floured board or aluminum foil. Knead until smooth and elastic. Place in a large greased bowl and cover tightly (also grease top of dough). Store in the refrigerator until doubled or until needed. Will keep 4 to 5 days. Punch dough down; turn onto floured board and knead again. Form into rolls and place in a greased pan. Let stand until doubled. Bake at 375° until done.

title: smoked turkey breast
directions: Mix all marinade ingredients and put in plastic bag with meat. Refrigerate overnight.
Remove turkey breast and wrap in large lettuce leaves.
Secure with toothpicks.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil with two layers.
Place on a hot grill with cover and cook on medium setting for 1 1/2 hours or until center is 165°.
Unwrap and discard lettuce.

title: remoulade sauce for seafood
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl; mix until well blended. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with cold boiled shrimp, crabmeat, lobster or tomatoes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: real easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Make your pie crust and roll it out; cut it into 3-inch strips and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. (Remember to pierce with a fork before cooking.)
Once crust is done, let cool.
Place one crust in bowl or plate; cover with strawberries and some whipped topping and repeat process.
Enjoy.

title: cream puffs
directions: Blend melted butter and hot water; put in small pan.
Bring to a boil and while boiling, stir in flour slowly.
Remove from heat and let cool.
When cool, stir in eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each egg.
Drop by spoonful on greased baking sheet and bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Fill with instant pudding when cool.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
You may even get clever and garnish the top with maraschino cherries and/or pineapple chunks.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender.
Cool. Alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion in dish. Combine remaining ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour mixture over the vegetables and refrigerate until needed. Yields 12 to 15 servings. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine 2 1/2 c. flour, sugar, syrup, butter, eggs, allspice and cloves.
Roll nuts, dates and raisins in 1/2 cup of the flour, and add last to batter.
Bake in 3 layers for 40 minutes.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, then take off bone. Cut into small pieces.
Add butter and soups. Top with dressing. Bake until bubbles all over at 350°.

title: mamas cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 475°. Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. In the meantime, heat the fruit. Add more fruit if desired. Now, mix flour, sugar and milk. Pour batter into melted butter. Add hot fruit. Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: smoked fish dip
directions: Mix.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover and chill.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
Serve with cracker or melba toast.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Roll into small balls and press down with a glass dipped in flour for each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Pour mixture over top.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Take out and mix again with spatula.
Put in oven again for 15 minutes.

title: one pan tuna and noodles
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add egg noodles and boil gently until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add tuna and cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Turn off heat.
Let stand on burner 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: corn bread
directions: Measure and sift (optional) mix together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add cornmeal.
In separate bowl, mix together the shortening, sugars, eggs and buttermilk.
Add wet ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Beat only until smooth.
Fill well oiled shallow pan 2/3 full (9 x 13 x 2-inch pan).
Bake in hot oven (400° to 450°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Various ovens may vary in cooking times.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: In a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper. Firmly press mixture across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and stir well.
Stir in nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: trail cake
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Beat together butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla, beat well.
Stir in oats, nuts, raisins and apples, mix well.
Press dough onto bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake 30- 35 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: In square baking dish, place margarine and uncooked rice.
Add soups, then add drained mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When taking out of oven, shake soy sauce to taste over rice and stir.
Serve hot.

title: three meat baked beans
directions: Brown
sausage;
drain.
Combine
beef and onion.
Cook until brown.
Drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients and bake in 2 quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tangy ham glaze
directions: Combine marmalade, mustard and ginger.
About 30 minutes before ham is done, brush it with about 1/2 of the glaze.
Add the orange juice to the remaining glaze.
Serve this mixture with ham after you simmer about 5 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Place a layer of potatoes in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Sprinkle with some onions.
Sprinkle some flour, salt and pepper over the layers.
Dot with butter.
Put some shredded cheese.
Repeat the layers until you use all the ingredients, ending with butter.
Pour milk over all.
Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Uncover; add some cheese. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: veg slaw
directions: Chop and mix together all the vegetables. In small bowl, mix vinegar, sugar, and Italian dressing. Pour over vegetable mixture. Add celery seed and salt and pepper. Ready to serve!

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes.

title: honey chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and heat.
Salt and pepper chicken and place in bottom of crock-pot.
Pour honey mixture over chicken and set crock-pot on low.
Let it cook all day.

title: black beans with rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans.
Let soak overnight.
Drain beans.
Cover with water 1-inch above beans.
Add 1 tablespoon plus 1 teaspoon garlic salt.
Cover pan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours or until tender.
Remove cover and simmer until liquid thickens.

title: shanty fried potatoes
directions: Put enough margarine in skillet to cover bottom.
Put shredded potatoes in skillet, cover and cook until brown.
Put margarine on top of potatoes before turning until it melts.
Turn potatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
After top is browned, remove from skillet and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add chocolate to milk; heat in double boiler.
When chocolate is melted, beat with rotary eggbeater to blend.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Add gradually to chocolate mixture and cook and stir until thickened.
Then cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour a small amount of chocolate mixture into egg yolks, stirring vigorously.
Return to double boiler and cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cover and cool. Turn cold chocolate filling in shell.

title: apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot with apples that are quartered and cored, but not peeled.
Add all ingredients.
Cook 3 hours on high.
Stir and cook 9 more hours on low.
Do not remove lid while cooking last 9 hours. Put 3 cups at a time in blender for a few seconds. Makes approximately 4 1/2 pints.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt, juice, flour and baking powder together.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour over sugar butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Invert plate over cake and turn cake out onto plate, pineapple side up.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour in bowl; add salt, oil and boiling water.
Stir with fork.
Dough will be soft.

title: roast pork with dried fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put 1 tablespoon flour in oven cooking bag.

Place pork and dried fruit in bag. Place bag in shallow roasting pan. Sprinkle in brown sugar and pour in the wine. Tie securely and puncture 4 holes evenly spaced across top of bag. Roast 1 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer reads 170°.
Slit bag open carefully to avoid escaping steam. Place meat on serving platter.
Spoon the fruit and cooking glaze over the meat.

title: herb stuffed veal loin
directions: Brown veal on each side 2 minutes; let cool.
Roll out dough. Spread 3/4-inch of stuffing evenly over it.
Place veal in middle; fold over and brush with beaten egg.
Bake in preheated 375 degrees oven 35 minutes.
Serve with Madeira Sauce and fresh vegetables. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken shirley
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in butter.
Mix soup and curry together, pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take chicken from pan.
Add large container of sour cream and mushrooms to the pan and mix well.
Return chicken to pan, sprinkle with almonds.
Return to oven for another 15 minutes.
Serve with rice or pasta.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add dressing.

title: summertime cake
directions: Mix ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Cool, then frost.

title: turkey noodle bar
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Put in cake pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine egg, shortening, sugar, cinnamon, milk and lemon juice.
Beat until creamy. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds.
Put peppers in blender.
Mix vinegar, sugar and peppers.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add Certo.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Drain.
Add cake coloring. Remove foam, pour in jars and cover with paraffin.

title: fluffy mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in thin slices.
Place with chicken broth and boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Mash potatoes with any remaining broth.
Add margarine, buttermilk and mix well.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Spread 1 1/2

cups crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Slice bananas over crumbs. Layer 1 1/2-inch slices of ice cream over bananas. Sprinkle nuts over ice cream. Put in freezer. Melt chocolate chips and butter. Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk; cook until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour chocolate mixture over ice cream. Freeze until firm. Spread Cool Whip and top with remaining cracker crumbs. Return to freezer. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: meat and rice casserole
directions: Butter a mold or loaf pan. Line 1/2-inch deep with 1/2 cup rice then pack in the meat mixture and cover with the rest of rice. Steam for 45 minutes.

title: venison meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place mixture in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3 inch casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour, 15 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a crock-pot. Cook for 5 to 6 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a pie pan.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Put cheese on top; bake 5 to 8 minutes more.
You can also use sliced cheese in place of shredded cheese, if you prefer to.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: championship chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl combine flour, sugar and cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chips.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: bear tenders
directions: Remove all fat from cubed bear meat.
Brown cubes in margarine.
Add pepper to taste.
Pour pineapple juice over meat, simmer 20 minutes.
Drain.
Coat with barbecue sauce.
Add water as needed.
Simmer in covered pan for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix shortening and egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop with teaspoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with Vanilla Filling.

title: orange sherbet pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add coconut and cook, stirring constantly, until golden, about 6 to 7 minutes. Remove from heat.
Reserve 2 tablespoons coconut for garnish. Press remainder into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Spread half of orange sherbet over crust.
Drizzle with liqueur.
Add remaining sherbet, mounding top.
Sprinkle with reserved coconut. Freeze until ready to serve or overnight.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish with mint, orange peel and mandarin orange segments.

title: humdingers(cookies)
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over Rice Krispies and nuts. Cool.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Add sugar and melted butter; mix well.
Add milk, flavoring, salt and spices.
Stir until well mixed.
Add eggs (slightly beaten) and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chocolate icing
directions: Melt oleo; add milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla; stir until fluffy. Spread on warm cake.

title: salsa dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Spread on bottom of baking dish. Spread cream cheese over sausage.
Spread salsa over cream cheese. Sprinkle cheese over top of salsa.
Bake at 320° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with nachos.

title: mexican kidney beans
directions: Saute onions in oil until crisp-tender.
Stir in tomatoes and kidney beans.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lime pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites in large bowl on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Beat egg yolks slightly in medium bowl. Beat milk, lime peel and lime juice into egg yolks.
Beat remaining ingredients into egg mixture until smooth.

title: wisconsin cake
directions: Mix cake, butter and 2 eggs.
Then line pan with this mixture (it will be very stiff).
Then mix cheese, sugar (reserving 1/4 cup), 2 eggs and vanilla.
Spread onto first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring until well blended.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll out into an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage (at room temperature) over dough, leaving 1/2-inch margin on all sides.
Carefully roll dough lengthwise, jelly roll style.
Pinch seams and ends to seal.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add alternately with sour milk.
Add vanilla and rhubarb.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle top with 1/3 cup sugar, mixed with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Nuts may be used in both cake and topping.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried turkey
directions: You will need a non-painted coat hanger and a 16 to 24-quart pot.
Recommended for cooking outdoors.

title: toasty french slices
directions: Spread bread with softened margarine on both sides.
Arrange in baking pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes until toasty and brown.
Serves 2.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix with mixer the cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust; chill.
Garnish with nuts.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add cream cheese and beat a few minutes.
Add sugar and cream for three minutes.
Add eggs and flour gradually until all is used.
Bake at 325° for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: surprise jello salad
directions: Soften the cream cheese.
Mix it with sugar until fluffy.
Set aside.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and allow to cool.
Scoop most of potato out, leaving shell intact.
Mix potato, cheese, butter, salt and pepper and put back into potato shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and pineapple.
Cook to hard boil. Take off stove and add orange jello.
Stir and let cool.
Add nuts, cherries (drained) and bananas.
Stir.
Pour into pie shells and chill.
Makes 3 pies.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Mix pepperoni, mushrooms, sauce, tomatoes and seasoning. Layer pasta, sauce mixture and cheese in 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: pete's ginger dressing
directions: Chop the ginger fine and mix all the ingredients together.
A must if you are serving salad with Oriental food.

title: blueberry pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put blueberries in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, salt, shortening, 3/4 cup sugar and milk together.
Pour over the berries.
Mix together the remaining 1 cup sugar and the cornstarch and sprinkle evenly over the batter.
Pour boiling water over the batter.
Do not mix.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or at room temperature with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: zesty hot sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve with favorite seafood.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: aunt helen's beet jelly
directions: Mix water and Sure-Jell; bring to a hard boil.
Add sugar all at once.
Bring to a full, hard boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add Kool-Aid and stir until dissolved.
Skim off foam and put into jars.
You can strain the beet water through a cloth for a nice, clean jelly.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix together lemonade and sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix eggs, corn and corn meal together.
Put 1/2 this mixture in a greased casserole dish.
Add cheese and green chilies and butter. Then cover with the leftover mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 450°.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Put in greased container, sprinkling potato chips on top. Bake 1/2 hour or longer at 400°, depending on size of container.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish.
Blend well.

title: thumb pies
directions: Mix flour, salt, margarine and water in bowl.
Form into little balls and place on cookie sheet and press thumb into each ball.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and fill thumb prints with jelly.

title: tuna fish loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add rest of ingredients and bake in buttered casserole in moderate oven about 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: karen's lemon chicken
directions: In a plastic or paper bag, combine flour, salt and pepper; shake to mix.
Add chicken, one piece at a time, and coat lightly. Save the remaining flour mixture.
In a skillet, warm 1 tablespoon of the oil over medium heat.
Add chicken and brown one side of chicken.
Add remaining oil and brown the other side of chicken.
Remove chicken.
Add butter and onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining flour; mix well.
Add broth, lemon juice and thyme; bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Return chicken to pan.
Reduce heat.
Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: diet asparagus soup
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth. Heat.

title: layered casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, then onions and meat.
Sprinkle with cheese. Make second layer and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sunshine shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender; process until smooth.
Chill before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: southwestern corn brunch
directions: In a bowl of warm water, thaw corn pouch for 20 minutes. Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
In medium bowl, beat eggs and stir in thawed corn, green chilies, cheeses, tomato, and chili powder; pour into baking dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserts 1 inch from center and comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
If desired, serve on lettuce leaf in a crisply fried tortilla.
Top each serving with sour cream and tortilla crumbs. Yield: 6 servings.

title: spicy banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large mixing bowl, mash bananas and mix with butter. Add eggs and water, mixing well.
Mix in dry ingredients until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes, until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mayonnaise cake with whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix together.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add peppers and onions, cooking until onions are soft.
Add beans, tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: hungarian beef stew
directions: Heat oil in a 5-quart kettle over medium-high heat; add meat, a few pieces at a time, and cook until browned on all sides.
Stir in broth, garlic and paprika.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender when pierced (about 1 hour).

title: jalapeno corn souffle
directions: In saucepan, combine water, cornmeal, butter, sugar, salt and pepper. Cook and stir until thick. Remove from heat and stir in milk, cheese, corn, jalapeno and pepper. Beat egg yolk until lemon colored. Stir into cornmeal. Beat egg white and cream of tartar to stiff peaks. Fold into cornmeal mix. Turn into ungreased 1-quart souffle dish. Bake in a 325° oven 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lemon apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine the ingredients, adding eggs one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt oleo; stir in flour, then milk.
Add salt.
Cook sauce until smooth and boiling.
Take off heat.
Add cheese.
Grease baking pan.
Fill alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Turn with spoon while baking for even cooking.

title: candy loaf
directions: Mix sugar, cream and syrup well.
Boil without stirring until it makes a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat as long as you can.
Separate in three parts.
Knead coloring into one part, a 1/2 cup of nutmeats in one part and the melted chocolate in the third part.
Knead as long as you can.
Place chocolate layer in bottom of buttered loaf pan, then the layer with nuts and the red layer on top.
Decorate with pecan halves.

title: colorful cabbage
directions: Fry bacon.
Add chopped cabbage and carrots.
Slowly add a bit of water.
Steam vegetables to desired tenderness.
Season to taste.

title: creamy hash brown casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add soup, cream cheese and salt.
Heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
In greased 2-quart casserole, place a layer of hash brown potatoes.
Top with a layer of cheese sauce.
Repeat layers, ending with a layer of cheese sauce on top.
Do not stir. Cover and bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender.
Uncover.
Top with cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes to melt cheese.
Serves 8 to 10. Great with steak.

title: baked bass
directions: Cut fillets into 6 servings.
Rub baking dish with shortening. Put fish in baking dish.
Mix onion, soup, salt and pepper; spread over fish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and put in an unbaked 8 to 9-inch pie shell.
Add enough milk to fill pie shell.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix with (clean) finger, being careful not to make a hole in pie shell.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) until a light brown.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in skillet; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat about 15 minutes.

title: l.b.j. cake
directions: Cream butter, flour and nuts.
Spread in a bowl.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.

title: oven "fried" chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine chicken and buttermilk in a shallow dish; cover and chill 15 minutes. Drain chicken and discard. Combine cornflakes and next 5 ingredients in a zip top bag. Add 4 pieces of chicken to the bag; seal the bag and shake to coat the chicken. Repeat the procedure with the remaining chicken. Spread oil evenly on a jelly roll pan and arrange chicken in a single layer. Bake at 400° for 4 minutes on each side or until done. Serve with a low-fat Ranch dressing, honey mustard or barbecue sauce. Kids love them! Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into balls size of marbles.
Flatten with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stolen pie
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet with onion. Drain fat. Spread layer of hamburger into the bottom of both shells, followed by a layer of cottage cheese, a layer of spaghetti sauce and a layer of cheese. Repeat this a second time so that there are two layers in each shell. Place both pies in the oven on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 425°, then for 40 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot or deep casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours (high for 4 hours).
Can be baked in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Combine and cook 20 minutes in microwave or 40 minutes in regular oven. Top with grated cheese.
This is an easy casserole to make.

title: rice, cheese, chili casserole
directions: Steam rice, then mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle top with some grated cheese.
Put in shallow Pyrex baking dish, baking 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Simmer ingredients 10 minutes, stirring often.
Spread sauce over pizza shells; add favorite toppings and heat.
Makes enough sauce for at least 4 large pizzas and it freezes great.

title: pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Let partially jell.
Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
(Use juice; do not drain pineapple.)
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and cheese to pineapple mixture.
Add this to thickened jello; fold in and refrigerate. Top with additional cheese and chopped nuts.

title: welsh rarebit(caws-wedi-pobi)
directions: Toast the bread.
Grate the cheese into a saucepan and heat gently until it melts.

Add the other ingredients and mix well. Spread over the toast and cook under the grill until brown. (Instead of precooking the cheese mixture, all ingredients can be mixed to a spreadable mixture and piled on the toast and then heated under the grill).
Garnish with parsley and serve at once. Serves 4.

title: diabetic triple bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large non-metallic bowl.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: marshmallow fudge frosting
directions: Mix margarine, milk, cocoa and marshmallows and stir over low heat until margarine and marshmallows are melted.
Remove from stove.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat well.
Spread over HOT Fudge Cake Squares while it is hot.
Cake must also be hot.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together ground chuck, Lipton onion soup mix and eggs to make medium meatballs.
Set aside.
In a very deep pan, mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured large tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until test done.

title: grandma wolf's snowballs
directions: Peel and mash cooked potatoes while hot.
Cool.
Add other ingredients and form into balls.
Drop balls into boiling water until they rise to the top of kettle.
Serve with gravy.
May be used like dumplings.

title: chocolate crunchies
directions: Melt chocolate in pan over hot, not boiling, water or microwave.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts. Mix well until noodles and peanuts are covered with chocolate. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Let stand about 30 minutes until hardened.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place meat in heavy saucepan like a Dutch oven.
Cover with hot water.
Cover tightly; simmer about 3 hours.
Skim off excess fat.
Add onions, carrots, potatoes, turnips and red sweet pepper. Cover; cook for 20 minutes, then add dill, fresh parsley and cabbage.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serves 8.
Serve cornbread muffins with it and a dish of fresh fruit.

title: mississippi mud cake microwave(serves 12)
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa together.
Remove from oven and stir in sugar and beaten eggs; mix well.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well. Spoon batter into greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cook 8 minutes on bake and 3 minutes on High.
Rotate while baking.
Sprinkle marshmallows on warm cake (you can return to oven 45 seconds to soften).
Cover with Chocolate Confectioners Sugar Icing.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed and drain. Brown ground beef, drain. Stir in tomato sauce and tomato paste. Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and cream in a separate bowl. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Layer bottom with noodles. Spread a layer of meat sauce. Spread a layer of the three cheese mixture. Sprinkle with mozzarella and cheddar cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cream wafers and creamy butter filling
directions: Mix butter, cream and flour (sifted).
Chill 1 hour.
Roll 1/3 dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Transfer to waxed paper heavily coated with sugar, turn to coat both sides.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Prick in 4 places with fork.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes or until slightly puffy.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Chop like pie crust.
Add in eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; fold into bowl with liquid ingredients.
Add chips.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: green pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Chill well to serve.

title: holly farm taters
directions: Wash potatoes.
Leave skins on.
Cut into quarters.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Rinse potatoes and roll in mixture until covered.
Place in baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake 30 minutes, uncovered, in a 425° oven.

title: coffee brandy
directions: Bring water, sugar and instant coffee to a boil, let cool, then add 1 quart vodka and vanilla; mix together.

title: graham cream torte
directions: Whip heavy cream with confectioners sugar and rum flavoring. Arrange 9 graham crackers in a square on a plate.
Spread with a thin layer of whipped cream.
Top with bananas.
Repeat 4 more times.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Frost sides and top with remaining cream.
Coat sides with chopped nuts, reserving a few for decoration on top.
Chill about 3 hours.
Cut into 9 squares.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in peanuts gradually so as not to lose boil.
Boil until peanuts pop and turn brown.
Remove from heat.
Add soda; stir well.
Pour on well greased platter.
I use cookie sheet.
Gives candy room to spread and easy to break in pieces when cool.
(You have to pour fast.)

title: ham filled potato salad
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water and onion to rolling boil; add potato flakes and set aside.
In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Reserve 1 egg for garnish; chop remaining eggs.
To mayonnaise mixture, add eggs, celery, pimento and mashed potato; stir to combine.
Slice reserved egg.
Line 1 1/2-quart bowl with Saran Wrap then arrange egg on bottom of bowl.
Spoon half of potato mixture into bowl.
Layer ham evenly over potato mixture and top with remaining potato mixture spreading evenly.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, unmold on serving plate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon crisp snack mix
directions: Break cinnamon crisp into bite size pieces.
Spread pieces, raisins, nuts and sunflower seeds on large 15 x 10-inch pan.
In small saucepan, melt butter with honey.
Drizzle over graham mixture.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan.
Loosen and store in airtight container.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together egg, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Have meat ground only once in a food chopper with a coarse blade.
Combine meats thoroughly in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs well.
Add onion and other seasonings and mix again.
Combine with meat and stir or knead until blended.
Pack into an oiled glass bread loaf pan and unmold on a flat baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 20.

title: four in one cookie(variety cookie dough)
directions: Mix on low speed until beaters gather dough together, about 2 minutes.
Gather dough into ball.
Cut into 4 equal parts.

title: mrs. beyer's stew
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add vegetables and soups. Season to taste with soy sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Mix soups, broth, onion, tomatoes and crushed chips.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chips, chicken and soups. Layer again with chips and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: easy barbecued ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces.
Boil for 45 minutes.
Put on baking sheet and pour barbecue sauce over them.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baseball bars
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and corn syrup together.
Add the peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well. Stir in the oats.
Press mixture into an oiled 9 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Spread with the hot topping. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Cool, then refrigerate.
Let stand about 15 minutes before cutting into pieces.

title: simple fish in foil
directions: You will need a 12 x 18-inch sheet of foil.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Melt butter and margarine.
Stir in flour, then add milk and cook until thick and bubbly.
Mix the remaining ingredients with the pasty mixture and pat into cakes.
Bread cakes in flour, egg and bread crumbs in that order.
Fry in hot oil until brown and firm, turning once.
Set on paper towel to soak up oil.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Delicious with any meal.

title: english trifle
directions: Prepare boiled custard, using 3 tablespoons of flour.
Spread all pound cake slices with preserves.
Line bottom and sides of trifle dish or glass bowl with some of pound cake.
Sprinkle with macaroon crumbs and 1/3 of sherry.
Cover with 1/3 custard. Repeat layers 2 more times, beginning with pound cake.
Cover; chill 6 to 24 hours.
Whip cream with confectioners sugar.
Cover Trifle with whipped cream; decorate with almonds.

title: cold pasta salad-pasta fredda
directions: * Recipe in this book.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Combine Jell-O and boiling water; add to pineapple and cook 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add cottage cheese, Cool Whip, lemon juice and chopped nuts.
Mix well. Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: punch bowl jello
directions: Mix Jell-O according to instructions; add to punch bowl and soft chill.
Add sliced strawberries and sliced bananas.
Chill to solid overnight.
Mix pudding according to instructions and chill overnight in a separate bowl.
Trim crust and cube angel food cake.
Add small Cool
Whip to pudding mixture, layer on Jell-O. (Mix together cake cubes, Cool Whip and pudding.)
Layer Cool Whip on top of Jell-O-pudding mixture and sprinkle with chopped pecans and decorate with fresh whole strawberries.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix and set aside the food coloring and cocoa.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and the color paste.
Beat 10 minutes.
Add buttermilk and slowly add flour, salt and vanilla. Remove from mixer and mix lightly the vinegar and soda.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) floured pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple tart
directions: In a small skillet, heat 3/4 cup sugar, stirring constantly, until it is liquefied and just golden.
Remove from the heat and quickly pour into a 10-inch pie plate.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine the flour, cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Arrange half of the apples in a single layer in a circular pattern in pie plate.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Arrange half of the remaining apples in a circular pattern over sugar.
Sprinkle with the remaining sugar mixture.
Place remaining apples over all, keeping the top as level as possible.
Dot with butter.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour until smooth.
Add water, carrots, bouillon and basil; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, squash and broccoli; cook 5 minutes.
Add half and half and pepper; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Serve over fettucini.
Garnish with cheese if desired.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper. Dip chicken pieces in melted butter and then coat heavily in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in a 9
x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining crumb mixture over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not turn chicken. Can freeze.

title: f. j. s. macaroni seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and rinse in cold water.
Drain well and place in salad bowl.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add to macaroni and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, except olives and tomatoes.
Toss gently.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: gram's applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, spices and chocolate; then add 2 teaspoons soda mixed in 1 cup water.
Add flour, raisins and nuts; mix well.
Add applesauce, mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Arrange in shallow casserole, covered with buttered crumbs. Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: easy white bread
directions: Heat over medium heat until warm the oil and milk.
Add egg and put mixture over the first 4 ingredients.
Add 4 to 5 cups more flour until right to roll.
Let rise and work down once, then roll into rolls or loaves of bread; let rise.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: shortbread cookie bars
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and flour and cream until smooth.
Use wrapper from butter to spread dough in cookie sheet.
Lay a piece of wax paper over top to help smooth batter evenly.
Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Beat egg white until stiff, along with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Spread over dough.
Sprinkle with fine nuts.
Bake at 275° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven at once.
Cut into squares.

title: jumbo chocolate chip ice cream cookie
directions: *You will need 2 aluminum pizza pie plates.

title: bay point squares
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cake mix and 2 eggs; stir to mix.
Pat
or
spread
in
dish.
Mix 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream
cheese;
pour
over
cake mixture.
Save some powdered sugar to go
on
top.
Bake about 40 minutes at 325°. Let set for a few minutes and cut into squares.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons water.
Combine 2 cups water with oil, flour and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Add yeast to batter, spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 24.

title: quick sweet treat
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Blend in the remaining 3 ingredients.
Quickly drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: joan crisp's pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into uncooked crust.
Bake at 300° until crust is golden or approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: easy tender brisket
directions: Line large pan with foil.
Place brisket in foil.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 bottle of hickory smoke and 1 cup of water over meat.
Close foil tightly.
Cook slowly at 250° for 7 to 8 hours.
Open foil, pour off all liquid and fat.
Pour barbecue sauce and remaining ingredients over meat.
Close foil tightly.
Cook slowly at 250° for 2 hours.

title: cheddar-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain macaroni.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain again. In mixing bowl, combine macaroni, cheese, celery, green pepper, peas and onion. Stir gently to combine.

title: sausage nibbles
directions: In bowl, combine biscuit mix, uncooked sausage and cheese. Mix with hands until completely blended.
Shape a little mixture to form a small ball (approximately 1 1/4-inches).
Place on baking sheet.
