Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen sausage balls.

title: mom's potato cakes
directions: Put egg in bowl and whip. Mix in potatoes. Add some flour so it will make a pancake in your hand. Fry in hot grease until brown on both sides.

title: spinach bites
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture. Combine spinach and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape spinach mixture into 3/4-inch balls; place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Can be frozen before baking.
Heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 11 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini with small amount of water until just tender, about 6 minutes.
Drain off water.
In bowl, combine eggs, mayonnaise, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over zucchini, stirring lightly to combine.
Mix crumbs and butter, sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Insert knife to test for doneness.)

title: microwave fat free tortilla chips
directions: Cut tortillas into wedges and place on paper towel.
Microwave for 3 1/2 minutes on High, or until crisp.
Remove and serve.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water, stir in 2 2/3 cups more warm water, sugar, salt, shortening and 5 cups flour, beat until smooth.

Mix in enough flour to make the dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured board, knead until smooth, about 10 minutes, place in greased bowl, turn greased side up, cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Punch dough down, divide in half, roll each half into rectangle roll up, beginning at short side.
With side of hand, press each end and seal, fold ends under loaf.
Place seamed side down in greased loaf pan. Brush loaves with butter, bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown ground beef with pepper and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cook for about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (not all of pineapple juice). Put in two unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Press the brick of cream cheese to the bottom of a pan.
Pour the can of beans on top.
Sprinkle both cheeses on top of that. Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with nachos.

title: nut cookies
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Add egg, sweet milk and flour, sifted with baking powder.
Then add salt and nutmeats. Mix thoroughly.
Drop on buttered tin and bake in moderate oven.

title: rita's chef salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Place salad greens in a large bowl.
Arrange meat in center.
Surround with shrimp.
Place mounds of peas, mushroom slices and cherry tomatoes on greens surrounding shrimp.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top of salad. Chill for an hour.
Use your own Blue cheese dressing.
Mix well and serve.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pans or use paper baking cups.
Mix corn muffin mix, egg and milk.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Let batter rest 3 or 4 minutes before filling cups.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Beat chicken with tenderizer and mallot.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
In a separate bowl, beat egg and add milk.
Lay out bread crumbs on a separate plate.
Dip chicken in egg milk mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Fry chicken gently until light brown.
Turn and brown other side; drain.
Put each piece of chicken in a casserole dish.
Pour pizza sauce over chicken, then mushrooms.
Finally, top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until sauce is hot and cheese melted.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a
large bowl, mix sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs; mix well. Add zucchini; stir.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour
into
2 (9 x 5-inch) pans.	Bake in a 350° oven for
to
90 minutes.
Top will crack when done.
Test with toothpick.

title: steamed mushrooms
directions: Bring broth to boil.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 4 to 6 minutes or until tender. Makes 2 cups.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix well.
Spread in shallow 10 x 10-inch serving dish.
Pour 1/2 bottle of chili sauce over the cheese mixture and spread evenly.
Sprinkle over the chili sauce 1 can of crab meat, drained and top with chopped parsley.
Serve with Ritz crackers and provide a butter spreader.

title: wadie's chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice, dry soup mix, canned soup and water in large casserole. Mix well. Lay chicken on top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: teriyaki chicken sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken or steak and soak overnight.
Turn meat occasionally.
Broil or barbecue meat.

title: sour cream pastry(for apple turnovers)
directions: Measure flour and sugar into a medium-size bowl.
Cut butter or margarine into mixture with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Add sour cream.
Mix lightly with a fork until dough clings together and starts to leave side of bowl clean.
Gather dough together with hands and knead a few times.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap or wax paper; chill several hours or overnight.

title: underwood holiday bells
directions: In small bowl, mix together cream cheese, ham, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; stir in bell peppers.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour and serve.
Makes 3 cups.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix other ingredients together and stir in macaroni.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a jelly roll pan with heavy-duty foil.
Place full layer of graham crackers in the pan edge to edge. Boil brown sugar and butter for 3 minutes.	Pour mixture over crackers and spread evenly.
Bake for 5 minutes or until all is bubbling and the crackers float.
Remove from oven and immediately lay Hershey bars on top.
Allow to stand for a minute to soften and then spread over top evenly.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts as desired and pat to set them in the chocolate.
Freeze 1 hour. Break apart to serve.
May be stored in freezer for later use.

title: sweet potatoes sonker
directions: Cook potatoes in water, sugar and vanilla; have the water over potatoes.
Butter your pan around the sides.
Make your dough as making biscuits.
Pinch off a little and pat out and line the pan with the dough that you have buttered.
Put your potatoes in the pan.
Put butter on the potatoes.
Cover the potatoes with some more dough.
When you have this covered, put more butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Put in oven and cook until it is good and brown.
Take out and put on top of the stove and let it boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of milk and let it boil for another 5 minutes.
When this is done, let it cool.

title: my favorite brownies
directions: Melt together the cocoa, butter and shortening.
Beat together the sugar and eggs; slowly stir cooled chocolate mixture into egg mixture.
Then add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake until top has a dull crust at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together; beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
DO NOT OVERCOOK.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring to a boil the large can of pineapple.
Add Jell-O; cool. Add buttermilk.
Let cool to jell set.
Mix in Cool Whip and add nuts.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook celery and onion in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer slowly.
Serve on buns.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all and cook in oven until brown.

title: easy salad
directions: Dice bananas and apples and mix with grapes.
No dressing needed.
Serves 2.

title: grosmommy's shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix.
Pour
into
unbaked
pie shells; top with crumbs. Bake at 400°
to
start,
then
turn back to 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Will be raised and bubbly.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour, chips and pecans. Mix well. Drop about 1 teaspoonful of batter about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten each drop by pressing with the bottom of a greased and sugared drinking glass. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: festive fruit pizza
directions: Soften dough and pat out in pizza pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake about 15 minutes until light golden brown at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled cookie. Arrange fruit in colorful pattern such as large strawberry in center and around outer ring, then rings of fruits.
Just before serving, put orange marmalade in bowl and add water to thin to a drizzle.
Cover fruit with drizzle, cut and serve.

title: skier's french toast
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar and corn syrup until sugar melts. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Layer cut up bread on top of syrup mixture in pan.
Mix eggs, milk, vanilla and nutmeg-cinnamon.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Serves 6.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: almond brittle
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan over low heat.
Add other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook, stirring constantly, until dark golden brown.
Spread onto buttered foil and let cool.

title: roast chicken with curry butter
directions: Mix garlic and all dry ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Gently loosen skin on breast, starting at neck.
Butter and put dry mix on.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: special punch
directions: Make gelatin in usual manner; add cold water and fruit juices. Stir in sugar.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: noel balls
directions: In medium sized mixing bowl, combine oats, 3/4 cup confectioners sugar, nuts, cocoa and orange peel.
Add orange juice and syrup, mixing until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened. Chill 1 hour.
Shape to form 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in 1/2 cup confectioners sugar; place in wax paper-lined container.
Store tightly covered at least 8 hours or overnight at room temperature. Roll each ball in remaining 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Store tightly covered.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen balls.

title: raisin bread
directions: Cook raisins and water together 2 to 3 minutes; cool.
Sift salt, soda, cinnamon and flour together.
Add sugar and egg to raisins.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Bake in a greased glass pan at 325° or in metal pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion, then mix others together.
Add hamburger and onion, pour into large baking pan.
Make corn meal as you would for corn bread and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until corn bread is done.

title: orange ice pop
directions: Fill ice tray with orange juice.
Cover it with aluminum foil. Stick popsicle sticks in.
Freeze for 1 1/2 hours.
Take aluminum foil off.
If not frozen, put back in freezer for 1/2 hour.

title: aunt millie's date nut bread
directions: You will need 2 standard size loaf pans.
Place all fruit in large heat resistant bowl.
Pour over hot water with baking soda dissolved in it.
Stir to break up fruit clumps; cover and set aside to cool for 2 to 4 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill a few hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, mix corn meal, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar until thoroughly combined. Make a well in center of the mixture. In a separate bowl, combine eggs, broccoli, cottage cheese and melted butter. Pour into well of flour mixture. Stir until just combined. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix with sliced apples and put into an 8 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter.

title: corn casserole - i
directions: Mix everything together. Pour into a buttered 7 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Brown beef and sausage, stir until melted real good.
Add salt, Texas Pete and oregano (to suit taste).
Spread on bread slices and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May top with pepperoni, grated cheese, onions, green peppers, mushrooms or other topping of your choice.
Makes 75 to 80 and can be frozen.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to boil.
Cook 3 minutes.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Gradually add the flour mixture, blending well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by tablespoonful 1-inch apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugars, margarine and vanilla pudding together.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chocolate chips and chopped nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown beef or chicken.
Add to stock pot with remaining ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are tender, and soup thickens up.
Serve with warm corn tortillas.

title: sourdough bread recipe
directions: Let starter stay out of refrigerator for 8 hours.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Boil soup, chili peppers and sour cream.
Remove from heat. Brown and crumble hamburger.
Fill tortillas with 2 tablespoons soup mix, a little hamburger, little cheese and onion.
Roll up and layer in pan.
Pour rest of sauce over pan of enchiladas and sprinkle with cheese.
Warm in oven about 20 minutes at 325°.

title: no crust miracle pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 (9-inch) greased pie pans.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook 30 minutes after it comes to hard boil and can in clear jars.
Makes about 9 to 10 quarts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in dates, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured loaf tins.
Makes 2 to 3 loaves depending on size of tins.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: bacon stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Dice bacon.
Fry until crisp.
Drain and cool on paper towels. Mix bacon, green onions and mayonnaise.
Cut thin slice off top of tomatoes.
Scoop out pulp.
Invert and drain on paper towels for 30 minutes.
Fill with bacon mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix butter, sugar and salt together.
Add eggs and vanilla extract to the sugar and butter mixture and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown sausage, onion and celery; drain.
Drain yellow and green beans.
Use whole cans of other ingredients.
Mix with tomato soup and paste.
Add mustard and brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
(You can also do in crock-pot on high for 3 hours.)
Makes a big pot!

title: copper pennies
directions: Cover carrots with water and boil 5 minutes.
Drain and cool. Into medium bowl, put salt, pepper and mustard.
Beat in a little of the oil to blend with mustard.
Add remaining oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and soup and beat again to blend.
Stir in onion, green pepper and carrots.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
Any marinade leftover may be kept in refrigerator and used as a salad dressing.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine the flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine the butter, both sugars and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: cracker snack
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Pour over crackers, then pour the oil over them. Leave on cabinet and go by and stir them all day until the oil is absorbed.

title: heavenly collards
directions: Saute onion and bacon or hog jowl together and set aside. Don't drain.
Wash collard leaves thoroughly.
To chop collard greens, just stack 7 to 8 leaves, roll them up and chop.
It makes chopping much faster.
In large pot, add collards to boiling water. They will all fit as they begin to wilt.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes after all collards are in pot.
Pour off water.
Cover collards with fresh water.
Add all other ingredients and cook 2 hours on low to medium heat.
Collards will cook down and almost all water will be gone.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Remove seeds and white portion of orange rind.
Grind together cranberries and orange, the rind and all.
Stir in sugar. Refrigerate in covered jars at least 2 days before serving.

title: chili con queso
directions: Heat chili without beans with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Blend well.
Serve in a chafing dish with corn chips.

title: linnea dittmar's cheese fluff souffle
directions: Put bread and cheese in buttered casserole in layers, with bread as top layer.
Beat other ingredients together; pour over bread and cheese.
Let stand at least 3 hours (or overnight) in refrigerator.
Bring to room temperature before putting in oven. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until firm.
Bake, covered, 1/2 of the time, then remove cover.
Serves 4 as a main dish or 6 to 8 as a side dish.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar until dissolved.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.

title: italian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add milk, sugar, salt, oil and half the flour.
Mix well. Add remaining flour and knead until dough forms a smooth ball. Allow dough to rise until double in size (about 1 hour).
Divide dough into two loaves.
Place on oiled cookie sheets. Allow to rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked lemon chicken with pasta
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the oil, lemon juice and seasonings in a shallow casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Roll the chicken in mixture and place in pan skin side down.
Put pan in preheated oven and cook until chicken is done (basting with juices).

title: apple dip
directions: Serve with sliced Granny Smith apples.	Also yummy with bananas and other fruit.

title: quick sweet and sour pickles
directions: Place pickles in a sterilized jar. Combine ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour solution over pickles. When cool, refrigerate. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: In a 1 quart jar with lid, add oil, salt, poultry seasoning, pepper and egg.
Mix
well.
Add vinegar and mix again.
Brush over chicken on grill or in oven.
Leftover sauce may be stored in refrigerator for about one month.

title: lentils and rice casserole
directions: Cook lentils according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain lentils and set aside.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; let it cool.
Punch plenty of holes into cake with a fork, making sure to hit the bottom of the pan.
Pour Jell-O over the cake slowly, allowing the mix to flow into the holes.
Spread the vanilla pudding on top and chill. Serve cold.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat margarine, 1 cup powdered sugar and vanilla.
Gradually mix in remaining ingredients until desired consistency.

title: miracle potato salad
directions: Add potatoes and salt to 1 quart boiling water.
Cook 2 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients. Toss.
You may garnish with 2 hard-boiled eggs (sliced), chopped lettuce, parsley and radish roses.

title: italian turkey
directions: Heat broth and soup with oleo until melted.
Remove from heat; add raw sausage, croutons, celery and onion.
Rub inside of turkey with sage leaves-garlic salt mixture.
With turkey in roaster, put dressing mixture on top of turkey (it falls off).
Add 2 cups water.
Cover with foil, making a tent.
Bake at 350° for 5 hours. Remove meat from bones and mix together with dressing mixture in roasting pan.
Serve on buns.
Makes a lot.
Delicious!

title: biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions and drain.
Combine cheese, soup and other ingredinets, except biscuits.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Remove and place biscuits around sides and top.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes until biscuits are brown.
Serve hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain. Combine sour cream, oleo, cheese, salt and pepper. Stir over low heat until melted. Take off. Add egg, onion and sausage. Add the squash. Place in casserole. Top with bread crumbs and oleo. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Add corn muffin mix. Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: oriental mix
directions: Cook rice.
Prepare skillet with butter or vegetable oil. Cook onions and ham.
Add rice.
Microwave 2 eggs and chop up into tiny pieces.
Cook peas.
Simmer.
Add eggs and peas into the skillet with the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown beef and onion in skillet; drain. Combine and put in large, flat baking dish all remaining ingredients.
Top with pizza toppings of your choice.
Add cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: boston circle cake
directions: Mix vanilla, sugar, water and egg yolks for a long time.
Then sift flour and baking powder.
Beat this on high speed.
Add a little at a time until all is in.
Then beat egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture.
Bake at 300°.
Makes two layer pans.

title: baked eggs
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add milk, cheese and corned beef.
Stir. Flavor to taste with Lawry's and onion salt.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: annie's potatoes
directions: Cook pepper for 6 minutes in boiling water.
Drain and mince. Add to potato cubes.
Add milk and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Put in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk, 2/3 cup cracker crumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimento.
Mix well. Turn into 1-quart casserole dish.

title: fluff
directions: Mix dry gelatin into cottage cheese until well blended.
Add whipped topping.
May add one can of drained fruit if desired. Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: jello pink punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sugar. Add all other ingredients.
Stir. Chill. Serves about 20 to 30 people.

title: grandma's christmas bread
directions: In bowl, pour boiling water over raisins and baking soda.
Let cool completely.
In large bowl, beat eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Add flour and raisin mixture, alternating back and forth to egg mixture in large bowl.

title: puffins
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk and butter.
Add flours, salt and cinnamon.
Mix on low speed just until smooth.
Fill greased muffin cups.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm, brown and lightly puffed.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: raspberry pudding
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, flour, baking soda and milk. Add berries to taste.
Pour mixture into square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, or microwave on High for 20 minutes. Texture will be like a cake.
May need more cooking time.
Check with toothpick in center of cake.

title: mexican turkey ole(light)
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet, spray pan with cooking spray.
Add the ground turkey, onion, celery, salt, cumin and garlic powder.
Cook until turkey is no longer pink and onion and celery are tender.
Stir in the tomatoes, beans, green chilies, corn and olives.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni; heat through.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Sprinkle flour in bottom of pan.
Add brown sugar, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir; watch for lumps.
Add chicken; turn to coat. Cut green pepper into slices; add to pan.
Add pineapple chunks. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until juices run clear.
Serve with rice.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Parboil pumpkin until tender, not soft.
Scoop out seed, then stuff with the following stuffing.
In oil, brown meat, then add onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fill pumpkin and bake, uncovered, at 350° about 30 minutes.
When serving, slice pumpkin and serve with stuffing.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans. Cover with water and soak overnight. Drain beans from water. Place beans, ham bone or ham shank, onion, carrots, celery, green pepper, tomato puree and clove in large pot. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Close cover securely. Cook until beans are tender. Good with cornbread.

title: one-pan fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in a 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Add milk, biscuit mix and sugar; stir until smooth.
Drop spoonfuls of filling over batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until deep golden brown.
The batter rises to the top as it bakes, forming a cakelike crust.

title: baked cavatelli
directions: Cook pasta.
Slice sausage into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Fry sausage.
Reserve 1 teaspoon fat from sausage to cook onion and garlic in.
Combine pasta, sausage, sauteed onion and garlic, tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce and half of the Mozzarella cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, covered. Uncover and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook for an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: low-fat apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix honey, applesauce, egg substitute, vanilla and milk.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Pour into a large loaf pan sprayed with Pam. Bake for 1 hour, or until a toothpick comes out clean.
(I just mix everything in the food processor, and it does fine.)

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger together.
Drain well.
Return to pan and mix in Cheez Whiz until all coated.

title: six week muffins
directions: * Let souring milk and vinegar stand at least 5 minutes before using.

title: nana's irish soda bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Stir.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: sweet chow chow
directions: Grind the tomatoes, cabbage, onions and peppers into a large pan. Add salt and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Put the drained vegetables into a large kettle and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Process in a water bath for 10 minutes.
Wait 2 weeks before opening.

title: fudge
directions: Open all four sticks of margarine, chocolate, milk and walnuts before you begin to have everything ready when you need it.

title: pot roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together in your crock-pot.
On medium setting, cook all day or about 8 hours.

title: hopping johns
directions: Drain and discard liquid from peas.
Saute sausage until done. Add onion; saute and drain.
Add to drained black-eyed peas and rice.
Season with Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Add cherry peppers. Serve as a main dish or as a side dish.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13 greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° until center is firm.
Serves 15.

title: skillet hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water to cover in a large saucepan until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, cool, peel and dice.
Place in a large bowl.

title: tennessee country bread stuffing for turkey
directions: Cook the sausage in skillet, breaking up with fork, as it cooks until all pink color is gone.
Pour off and discard all but 1/2 cup of liquid.
Add celery and onion to sausage in skillet. Add in salt, pepper, basil and oregano, stirring to mix well.
Put bread in a large bowl and add sausage mixture, parsley and enough chicken broth to moisten.
Mix together.
Will stuff one (12 to 14 pound) turkey.
Bake excess in ungreased casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine corn, buttermilk, oil and eggs; mix well.
Stir in cornbread mix.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with green chiles and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour remaining 1/2 of batter over top and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: punch(diabetic)
directions: Mix orange juice as directed on can. Add pineapple juice and almond flavor. Keep in refrigerator. This recipe is very good.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in oil until transparent and thoroughly cooked. Add broth and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Divide into 6 oven-proof soup bowls.
Top each with a slice of toasted French bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place in broiler until cheese melts.
Serves 6 people.

title: plum loaf
directions: Mix well and bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dates and vanilla,
in a saucepan.
After this begins to boil, add dates.
Cook until it jells.
Add vanilla; beat until cool and creamy.
Pour on wet cloth and roll up.

title: chicken  casserole
directions: Add
soup, Veg-All and chicken, salt and pepper.
Top casserole with pie crust.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In large pot of water add onions, celery, carrots, and green peppers.
Bring to a boil.
When carrots are soft, add tomatoes, cabbage, and beef.
When cabbage is soft, add green beans without juice and kidney beans with juice.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: In large pot, combine tomatoes, juice, salt and sugar.
Bring to boil.
In small bowl, combine baking mix and milk.
Mix until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling tomatoes.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: rice cereal
directions: Put Minute rice in bowl; pour on hot water.
Let set for 5 minutes, then check and pour out any access water.
Add milk like you would in cereal.
Add your sugar and anymore you need.
Then add vanilla flavoring.
Stir.

title: nippy franks
directions: Cut wieners into 3rds.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crock pot.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.
Remove lid and cook 2 to 3 more hours.
Enjoy!

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken 45 minutes or until cooked thoroughly.
Debone and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Lay chicken on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare broccoli as indicated on bag.
Cut into bite-size pieces and layer over chicken.
Drain mushrooms and place over broccoli.
Shred or slice Velveeta cheese and layer over mushrooms.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Top casserole with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mamie june's fruit cake
directions: Cook apples with baking soda.
Set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, mix brown sugar, oleo, eggs and milk.

In a separate bowl, sift together flour, cocoa, allspice, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon, then a little at a time, blend flour mixture into other bowl until well mixed. Add nuts, cherries, dates and pineapple.
Mix well. Last thing, add cooled, cooked apples; mix well.
Pour into well-greased angel food cake pans.
Makes enough cake batter for 2 cakes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips, fajitas or Mexican egg dishes.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cool eggs under cold running water 5 to 10 minutes.
Peel shells from eggs.
Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Mash yolks with remaining ingredients except paprika until mixture is smooth. Fill whites with this mixture; sprinkle with paprika.

title: bluegrass music snack
directions: Slice bagel in half.
Spread on cream cheese.
Put on salmon. Top with other half of bagel.
Serves 2.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into 2 to 3 (9-inch) deep-dish pie crusts.
Bake in 375° oven 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cheddar biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. Brush with butter and spices. Bake as you would regular biscuits.

title: squash dressing
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 8 x 13-inch dish.

title: roquefort skinny dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a food processor or blender; mix.
May be used as a salad dressing.
Makes 1 cup.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Mix Jell-O together.
Add blueberries and pineapple to Jell-O mixture and refrigerate until firm.

title: mom's quick cherry pie
directions: Butter bottom of large casserole pan.
Pour pineapple and pie filling in pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix, then nuts.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add into shortening mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger until brown; add onion.
Cook until brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: tofu soupdallas, texas
directions: Boil chicken or vegetable stock.

title: microwave zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add oil and zucchini; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour into large microwave Bundt pan.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; rotate dish.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes longer or until bread begins to pull away from sides.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before turning out of
pan.
Frost if desired.

title: adobo(a filipino dish)
directions: Cut up chicken and pork into chunk size pieces.
Put into large pot along with soy sauce, vinegar, bay leaves and pepper. Slow cook, covered, for 1 hour until meat is tender over medium heat.
Remove meat.
Add diluted cornstarch to pot.
Turn heat up to high.
Stir until thick.
Remove from heat and place meat back into pot.
Cook rice.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all together by hand.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry whipped cream cake
directions: Bake the cake mix according to directions on the box. (Slightly freeze the cake in order to slice into three layers.)

title: scalloped corn
directions: Add whipped eggs to creamed corn; next add crushed Ritz crackers.
Mix well all 3 ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking dish for 1 hour at 350° or until center is done.

title: oklahoma brown candy
directions: Place sugar for caramelizing in heavy skillet.
Place 4 cups sugar and milk in large, deep heavy kettle.
Caramelize sugar in skillet over low heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon as it melts slowly and becomes a syrup about the color light brown sugar.
When sugar begins to melt, place kettle with sugar and milk mixture over low heat.
Let this simmer as you continue stirring the melting sugar.
When syrup is light brown, pour in a very fine stream into kettle of simmering mixture, stirring all the time to blend.
Cook and stir until mixture reaches a firm ball stage (244° to 248°).

title: rosy rhubarb preserves
directions: Combine rhubarb, pineapple and sugar.
Cook over low heat to dissolve sugar, then cook 10 minutes over medium heat.
Continue to cook slowly until mixture thickens and is clear.
Add jello.
Pour into jars and seal.
Keeps well in refrigerator or freezer.

title: pizza dunks
directions: Slice bread lengthwise, then into strips and finally into cubes about 1 to 2-inches square.
Place on cookie sheet and heat in a 425° oven until tan.
Remove and put in a bread basket.
Put sauce in baking dish and heat in microwave until hot.
Remove and sprinkle cheese on top.
When cheese melts, put on table with bread.
Give each child a fork and let him or her stab a cube of bread and dip it into sauce.
No mess and no waste!

title: jamaican sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water until barely tender; cool to handle.
Remove skin and slice into medium slices.
Saute onion in butter and curry.
Add salt, pepper, raisins, broth, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Place potatoes and combined mixture in casserole and bake at 350° until half of the liquid is absorbed.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: sue's chili dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese over bottom of quiche dish or other shallow casserole dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese. Sprinkle Jack cheese over chili.
Bake in microwave or conventional oven until hot and bubbly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first.
Mix mayonnaise, water and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Bake in oblong pan at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: christmas cocoa
directions: Combine, mixing well.
To serve, combine 1/3 cup dry mix and 1 (8 ounce) cup hot water; stir.
Makes about 4 quarts or 48 servings.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Deep	fry
in hot oil (375°). Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.	When
brown on one side, turn and brown other side.
Makes 15 to 20 small puffs.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Put all ingredients in boiler and let come to a boil.
Let simmer until mixture thickens. Spread between layer and on sides of cake.

title: coffee cake(monkey bread)
directions: Melt 1 stick butter. Add brown sugar and chopped pecans. Roll each individual dough ball in mixture. Grease Bundt pan. Put rolled dough balls in Bundt pan. Put cloth over pan to keep air off dough. Let set overnight to rise.

title: wild rice
directions: Cover rice with water, about 1/2-inch over.
Simmer until water is absorbed.
Add consomme and diced onion and celery.
Cook until consomme is absorbed.
Add mushrooms and butter.
Heat through.

title: stir-fried chicken and vegetables
directions: In skillet, saut onions and garlic in oil for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and cook 2 minutes more or until chicken is cooked through. One at a time, add broccoli, pepper and mushrooms, sauteing each for 1 minute before adding next ingredient.
Add soy sauce, ginger and parsley to chicken/veggies.
Reduce heat; cover and steam 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir and serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts (bake or boil) and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix soups, sour cream and chicken; pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Sprinkle this over the chicken mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bake empty pie shell at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine all ingredients including 1/2 of the Durkee onions.
Pour this mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining Durkee onions on top and return to oven 5 more minutes.

title: lemon noodles with peas
directions: Bring water and butter to boil in a medium saucepan.
Add noodles and butter sauce.
Continue boiling 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in peas and lemon peel.
Cook for 3 more minutes.
Cover and let sit for about 5 more minutes.
Serve.

title: stuffin' muffins
directions: In large bowl cream Ricotta, applesauce, fruit sweetener and oil.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
In separate bowl combine flour, wheat germ, soda, baking powder, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to batter; blend well.
Add zucchini, apples, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Spoon into 15 muffin cups which have been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes (or until firm and golden brown) at 350°.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: blueberry-orange nut bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Mix in eggs, milk, orange juice and grated orange peel.
Stir until well blended.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until blended.
Fold in blueberries and walnuts.
Spoon batter into pan. Bake one hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and salt.
Let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour over cucumbers, onion and peppers.
Let stand overnight.
Store in containers in refrigerator.
Will keep for months.
No need to seal.

title: summer's best barbecue
directions: Marinate the chicken in the brown barbecue sauce overnight. Remove the chicken from the marinade and grill.
As the chicken is being grilled, baste with the following Red Barbecue Sauce.

title: quick and easy dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and add warm water if needed to make dressing right moistness.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Bake at 350° until dressing is browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Blend the other ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add the egg mixture to the dry ingredients.
Prepare bread loaf pans:
spray with nonstick cooking spray; flour.
Pour mixture into prepared pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for one hour (or until light brown).
Test with toothpick. Butter top.
Cool on wire rack for 20 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, pineapple and bread.
Put in margarined baking dish and bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.
Good hot or cold.
Especially good as a ham accompaniment.

title: cheddar bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in 1/2 stick butter. Add, after mixing, milk and egg.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased loaf pan.

title: johnnycake
directions: In a heavy-based pan over low heat, dissolve the sugar with the molasses, spices and butter.
Slowly and carefully bring the mixture to a boil.
Cool it to room temperature, then mix in the baking powder.
Place the flour in a bowl with a pinch of salt and make a well in the center.
Pour in the cooled syrup mixture and the egg and stir from the center to incorporate the flour.
Turn the dough out onto a floured surface and knead, then wrap it in wax paper and refrigrate it for about 30 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Weigh the pears after peeling before grinding. Stir in the sugar.
Cook 30 or 40 minutes. Add the pineapple. Cook 30 minutes or longer to thicken.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix together well.
Cook in well-buttered muffin tins half full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour stem pan.
Melt candy bars and syrup; cool.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add chocolate mixture, pecans and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes, then turn out on cake plate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Add soup, pepper and onion to mixed rice and broccoli.
Put in casserole and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: congealed jello pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to instructions on package using juice plus enough water to make 4 cups of liquid.
Mix pineapple and Miracle Whip until smooth.
Stir into Jell-O.
Pour into square Pyrex dish, let set.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in order. Drop by tablespoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Cook for 15 minutes. Cookies can be frozen. Double recipe for a monster batch.

title: mock lemon meringue cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Put in a 10-inch tube pan. Cool.
Split cake into three layers.
Stir pudding until smooth. Spread 1/3 of filling between each layer and on top of cake.
Frost sides and top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water until just tender, not soft.
Drain well and place in a heatproof serving dish over low heat.
Toss the pasta in the butter until melted.
Add the cheese and cream a little at a time, mixing lightly with 2 forks, until the cheese melts and the noodles absorb the cream.
Add pepper to taste.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil stewing hen until very tender.
Debone the chicken.
Add water to broth to equal about 2 quarts of broth.
Bring to simmer boil.
Add strips of rolled dough, a few strips at a time.
Press dough into the broth and simmer each time, adding more strips of dough.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour or so, stirring occasionally.

title: shortcut cinnamon buns
directions: Let loaves of frozen bread dough rise, then roll out dough. Cover rolled out dough with layer of butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar mixture.
Roll into jelly roll.
Cut into one-inch slices.
Place in deep pan.
Let rise again.
While buns are rising, put 2 pounds powdered sugar, 1 cup water and stick of butter on stove on medium-high until sugar is melted, then pour over top of buns until completely covered.
Put in oven at 350° until brown.
While still hot, flip into another pan.
Put foil over top to keep fresh.

title: low-fat yellow cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare a 12 cup Bundt pan with vegetable spray and flour.
In large bowl of electric mixer, blend cake mix, water, baby food and eggs on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Turn batter into prepared pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in pineapple juice and 1 1/2 cups of water. (Do not drain.)
Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Add gelatin to hot cranberries after crushing them.
Add sugar and let get cold.
Then add pineapple, seeded grapes and pecans.
Then chill.
Serve.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Place all ingredients, except cheese and meat, in blender and mix for 4 to 5 seconds.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle cheese and meat over top and push gently below surface.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: deep pan pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add tomatoes and pizza sauce from mix.
Simmer.
Prepare crust mix as directed and press into 9 x 13-inch pan; press on bottom and sides.
Put layer of meat, layer of cheese and layer of meat.
Put cheese from mix on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine orange and lemonade concentrates and sweetened condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables and cool.
Drain.
Add onion, celery, Miracle Whip and shredded cheese.
Mix well and pour into dish. Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over this.
Bake 30 minutes in 325° oven.

title: old-fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash, hull, drain and crush strawberries.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut 1 stick of butter with pastry blender.
Mix with fork, adding enough milk to make a soft dough.
Stir to blend.
Beat rapidly for 1 minute, until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead gently for 30 seconds.
Divide in half and with floured hands, spread each half over the bottom of inverted 8-inch cake pan.
Prick surface with fork.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden.
When cakes are done and still hot, spread 1 layer with remaining butter.
Put layer on serving plate, buttered side up and spread with half the strawberries.
Top with second layer and remaining strawberries.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: defense cookies
directions: Blend white and brown sugars.
Cut in shortening; mix well. Sift flour; measure, then add soda and salt.
Sift again.
Stir flour well into shortening and sugar mixture.
Beat egg well; add to sugar, shortening and flour mixture.
Add vanilla, then morsels.
Have cookie pans well-greased and floured.
Drop from teaspoon about an inch apart.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Yields 36.

title: no bake cookies(not chocolate)
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in pan; bring to boil 1 minute. Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by the tablespoon on waxed paper.
Wait for them to firm up.
You should be able to take them right off the waxed paper after they have cooled down.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and walnuts.
Bring to boiling; remove from heat.
Stir in salad oil; cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients; beat into raisin mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: caesar salad
directions: Salt bowl, then mince garlic.
Ring bowl with Worcestershire sauce (1 teaspoon); add mustard.
Add oil, vinegar, egg and lemon. Beat well.
Add lettuce, pepper, cheese and croutons.
Toss well; serve on chilled plates.

title: rainbow sherbet dessert
directions: Whip cream until frothy.
Add sugar and vanilla, beating until soft peaks form.
Fold in macaroons and pecans.
Spread half of mixture into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Freeze.
Spread a layer of each sherbet over whipped cream mixture, allowing each layer to freeze before spreading next layer.
Top with remaining whipped cream mixture.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from pan and place on serving plate.
Garnish with strawberries.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crusty potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a shallow baking dish with cooking spray.
Cut potatoes into wedges.
Combine mustard, paprika, cumin and garlic salt.
Add potatoes and toss.
Make sure the potatoes are well coated.
Spread in baking dish in single layer.
Bake 10 minutes; turn once.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until tender and crusty.
Serves 4.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix water and baking soda.
Stir in molasses and egg yolk. Pour into pie crust.
Mix flour, sugar, margarine and spices with your hands until just crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over filled pie crust.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325°; continue to bake until browned, about 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Delicious with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vinegar in a large bowl; mix well.
Add other ingredients and stir until all is covered with juice.
Cover and keep in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Will keep for at least 1 month.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef until browned.
Stir to crumble.
Drain.
Add taco sauce
mix,
corn and beans; blend well.
Cool slightly. Layer half the chips, meat mixture, lettuce, cheese and tomatoes	in serving bowl.
Repeat layers.
Serve with taco sauce. Yields 6 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and slice eggplant; place in a 2 x 14-inch cooking dish and salt to taste.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Dip eggplant into flour and put in egg mixture; fry until brown, then place back into cooking dish in layers.
Sprinkle each layer with Parmesan cheese and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes until hot.

title: sunday supper salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, grapes and nuts in large bowl.
Blend mayonnaise or salad dressing, parsley, lemon juice and salt in small bowl.
Toss seasoned dressing with chicken mixture; chill. Line salad bowl with lettuce and romaine leaves.
Pile chicken mixture in center.
Wreath outer edges of salad with cranberry sauce cubes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and mix with eggs.
Beat cream of celery soups, grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Pour in 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mike's favorite ground beef and vegetable stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef, breaking up pieces with spoon. Add onions, garlic, water, basil, salt, pepper and potatoes. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add peppers and tomatoes; simmer for 10 minutes or until all is tender.
Serve in bowls.
Serves 4.

title: pan barbecued steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak. Brown in shortening. Remove meat from pan. Cook onion and celery in pan until tender. Return meat to pan.
Mix remaining ingredients to make a sauce.
Pour sauce over steak. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. This is great with rice.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll out 1 loaf frozen bread.
Layer with pepperoni, Provolone cheese and American.
Roll up; tuck in edges.
Mix egg, shaker cheese and oregano together.
Brush on bread.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: flan
directions: Caramelize 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Pour into aluminum or stainless steel 2-quart round pan.
Beat together 8 eggs.
Add 8 tablespoons sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Pour into pan with caramelized sugar.
Place in pan of water.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sinful sundae pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of a buttered 9-inch pie plate with vanilla wafers.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add margarine; mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remaining mixture onto bottom of pan; bake for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add sugar and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg. Add warm water.
Stir in dissolved yeast mixture and beat in flour.
(You may need to add a little more flour to make a fairly stiff dough, but not too stiff!)
Place dough in a bowl, cover and let rise until doubled. Press down and put in refrigerator.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Cream butter with sugars until blended.
Add egg, vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and oats. Stir; add chips, nuts and raisins.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: milk punch
directions: Mix milk and 1-quart of ice cream until smooth.
Add your choice of fresh fruit or fruit juice to taste.
Float additional ice cream in punch.
Makes 32 (4 ounces) servings.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; beat well.
Stir in chocolate chips; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients in large container that you can store it in, also.
To make a serving of hot cocoa, use 1/4 cup to 1/2 cup of mix in cup and add boiling water.
Stir and add marshmallows, if desired.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator when ready to serve; remove garlic.

title: cheesy bread fingers
directions: On a lightly floured surface, roll bread dough to a 13 x 9-inch rectangle.
Place dough in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover; let rise in warm place about 1 1/2 hours or until nearly double.
In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in seasoning.
Cool mixture slightly; stir in cheese.
Spoon cheese mixture evenly atop dough.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Serve warm.
Makes 24.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of hot water; chill until partially jelled.
Fold in remaining ingredients; chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal, oil, and eggs into cake mix, mix well.
Drop by tsp. on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes.

title: butter-pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in melted butter, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until toasted.
Set aside to cool.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in a covered, airtight container.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine cooked chicken, grated onion, celery, mayonnaise, lemon juice and slivered almonds.
Turn into greased baking dish. Combine Cheddar cheese and croutons.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: tricky teriyaki chicken
directions: Skin chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, combine orange soda, reserving 1 tablespoon and soy sauce. In separate cup, mix cornstarch and 1 tablespoon orange pop to make a paste.
Add paste to the soda and soy sauce mixture.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator and then bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning chicken a few times.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes.
Place paper towels in microwave.
Cook potatoes on High 15 to 18 minutes, until soft when pierced. Rearrange once or twice.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes.
Peel potatoes.
In a large bowl, melt margarine on High 45 to 60 seconds.
Add potatoes and mash thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients and mash thoroughly.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole and microwave on High 5 minutes.
Reduce power to Medium and microwave 8 to 12 minutes.
Garnish with orange slices and almonds.

title: fried apples
directions: Wash,
quarter
and core apples.
Slice into the skillet where bacon
or
sausage
has been cooked.
Butter may be used instead of bacon or sausage.
Turn the apples often to prevent burning. When
the apples begin to soften, sprinkle with white or brown sugar.
Apples are ready when they are brown.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli over medium heat until tender.
Melt butter in a 2-quart pot and add onion, cook until glossy.
Add flour and stir until mixed well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Add bouillon cube, pepper, salt and cooked broccoli.
Cook over medium low heat until slightly thickened.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Prepare gelatin according to package directions.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mash strawberries.
Add to gelatin mixture. Add yogurt, sugar and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 4 (1/2-cup) molds coated with cooking spray.
Chill until set.
To serve, unmold onto salad plates.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: dangerous fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in microwave-safe bowl.
Make a well in center.
Stand cube of butter on end in well and pour milk around the well.
Put in microwave and nuke on High for 2 minutes.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch dish (Pam it!) or pie plate.
Chill and eat!

title: tortellini all forno
directions: In large saucepan, stir together butter, ham and mushrooms. Heat about 3 minutes.
Add cream and stir.
Make sure it does not stick.
Three to five minutes before tortellini is done, add flour and water.
These 2 items make the thickening sauce.
Add Parmesan or Romano.
If mixture is too thick, add milk or white wine.
Use 2 individual Corning-type casserole dishes (6 inch deep x 12 inches in diameter), square or round.
Layer, starting with sauce, tortellini, sprinkle of cheese and 1 slice of Provolone.
Repeat, for a total of 2 layers.
Cook at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 2 healthy Italian servings.
Serve with tossed salad and garlic bread.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: Combine 2 sugars and 2 cups water.
Bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in coffee.
Cool.
Pour in tall jug or jar.
Add vodka and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Cover and let stand at least 2 weeks.
Remove vanilla bean.

title: applesauce deluxe
directions: Dissolve Jell-O gelatin in boiling water.
Blend in applesauce and lemon juice.
Chill until firm.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix everything together (except tortillas).
Spread over tortillas.
Roll up.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
To serve, slice and place flat on platters.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Cover bottom of pie shell with Swiss cheese.
Wash and drain the crabmeat and arrange evenly over the cheese.
Sprinkle bacon and crushed red pepper (to taste) over them.
Drain artichoke hearts.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and add.
Combine eggs and half and half and pour evenly over the filled crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Top evenly with Monterey Jack cheese, then bake at 350° for 30 minutes (until fork inserted in the middle comes out clean).

title: pierce's soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in warm water.
Blend in sifted flour.
Knead on lightly floured board, 15 to 18 times.
Let rest 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat all together and spread.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll mix, flatten like a pizza.
Put on the top 6 or 8 ham slices and Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll in tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Coarsely chop cranberries by hand or in a food processor. Combine cranberries, orange juice and zest, sugar and salt in stainless steel pan.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer until thickened, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before adding walnuts.
Cool completely before refrigerating in a covered jar.

title: my grandmother turner's pound cake(over 100 years old)
directions: Have butter soft.
Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and other ingredients gradually.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Boil egg noodles, drain and rinse with cold water.
Add mixture to noodles in 6 x 12-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quick company chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breasts in dressing for 1 to 3 minutes. Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add chicken breasts, Italian dressing and mushrooms.
Cover and cook over medium to medium-high heat until chicken is cooked through, about 15 minutes.
Serve, spooning the dressing and mushroom over the chicken breasts.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Place halved tomatoes on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle on cheese. Place under broiler for about two minutes.
Can be topped also with any of your favorite dried herbs.
Example:
Use Parmesan cheese and basil.

title: indian babouti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef without adding fat to pan.
Add onion; saute 3 minutes.
Add flour and curry powder.
Mix well. Remove from heat; add stock, raisins, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Put into baking dish.
Soak diced bread in milk 30 minutes.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve with rice and salad.

title: chunky barbecue beef(serves 8)
directions: Brown meat in skillet sprayed with vegetable pan spray.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours, adding water if necessary.
Serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: hot sauce
directions: Simmer in saucepan and add onion, salt and garlic and add juice of tomatoes.
Cut up tomatoes, then add to sauce.
Simmer about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend well. Mix in oats, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: In medium saucepan combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in Marshmallow Fluff, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Remove from heat and pour into small square pan.
You should line pan with wax paper.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: egg and sausage puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix together with hands:
melted butter, graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Put on cookie sheet and smooth with back of spoon.

title: fruit and glaze salad
directions: If you use strawberry glaze, save red cherry liquid.
If you use peach glaze, save liquid from 1 can of oranges.
Mix pie glaze and liquid together.
Mix all fruits together.
Combine both. Cover and chill.
Will keep well.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Place fillets in a Ziploc bag and roll with rolling pin to flatten slightly.
Place fillets on waxed paper.
Put 1 ounce cream cheese on fillet and roll up.
Wrap with 2 strips of bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Beat eggs and water.
Dip roll-ups into egg wash.
Dip into bread crumbs.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Very good!

title: symphony brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix according to directions.
Spread half of mix in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Layer candy bars on mixture.
Top with remaining mix and cook as directed.
Allow to cool prior to slicing.
Very rich.
Good with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut and squeeze juice from lemons.
Add to water in large pitcher.
Stir in sugar and ice cubes.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: granola bars
directions: Combine oats, peanuts, sugar, wheat germ, raisins and vanilla. Stir well.
Add Egg Beaters and margarine.
Press into bar, use a 9 x 9 x 2-inch tin to place them on.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes approximately 16 bars.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix together.
Knead and shape into rolls.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Check after 10 to 15 minutes.

title: special bean rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain, add beans, chillies and picante sauce.
Fold into tortillas, sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave 1/2 to 1 minute.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add milk and vanilla and mix.
Stir in flour and baking powder; mix well, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch square pan at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sponge cake
directions: Cream margarine, add sugar.
Add one egg at a time beating after each addition.
Add flour, stirring well.
Add vanilla, pour into a tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: tex-mex chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Cut wings at joints; discard tips. In large skillet, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, cook chicken, about 8 minutes on each side or until no longer pink when cut into.
Stir in chili sauce, vinegar, chilies, pepper sauce, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes until sauce thickens.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Add and mix ingredients together, one at a time.
Use as dip for raw vegetables such as broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, cucumbers and peppers (any raw vegetable).

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in butter, milk and egg yolks. Stir well.
Cook slowly, until desired thickness.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue made from egg whites.
Cook at 400° until meringue is browned.

title: walnut mocha cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add coffee infusion alternately with flour, sifted with baking powder.
Add nuts and egg whites, beaten stiff.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix together and form into patties.
Roll in 1 egg and cracker crumbs.
Deep fry at 375°.
Serve with creamed peas.

title: green beans parmesan(serves 4)
directions: Microwave 1 tablespoon of margarine in a 1 cup glass measuring cup for 20 to 30 seconds (until melted).
Add bread crumbs and cheese.
Microwave 45 to 60 seconds or until golden brown and crisp.
Cook green beans and onion in covered saucepan with 1/4 cup water until tender.
Drain.
Toss with other tablespoon of butter.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in 8-cup bowl.
Add milk and margarine. Do not stir.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add peanut butter and beat.
Pour out and cool.

title: cheesy breakfast casserole
directions: Place one pack of crescent rolls on bottom of pan pressing together for shell.
Saute sausage, drain, and pat off grease. Combine sausage w/cream cheese and spread over crescent rolls.
Top with the other package of crescent rolls pressing seams together. Bake for about 20 min. at 350°; then add all the cheddar cheese you want to cover top, and bake until cheese melts.
It's easier to use shredded cheddar.
Or you could half mixture with a smaller pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump first three ingredients into shallow 2-quart baking dish. Do not mix. Sprinkle with dry cake mix and dot with butter. Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until crusty.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: eggplant caviar
directions: Put a whole eggplant in a 400° oven and bake until soft, about 1 hour.
While cooking eggplant, peel and chop one large onion, green pepper and peel and chop 2 tomatoes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well and shake in jar.

title: dressing for chicken or turkey
directions: Crumble the bread in a large bowl.
Simmer the celery and onion in the melted margarine until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients to the crumbs and mix.
The mixture should have the consistency of uncooked cornbread.
Bake in greased pan at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix and pour into frozen tart shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8-10 shells.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray oblong pan with Pam; spread the nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Pour cake mixture over coconut and pecans.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together and pour over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cake will crack while cooling.

title: pear and peach pickles
directions: Heat these ingredients to boiling.
Drop fruit in and boil until tender.
Put in sealed jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: broccoli-noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, stir together soup, cheese, mushrooms and milk.
Lightly toss the hot pasta with soup mixture and broccoli.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Cover; bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Drain potatoes. Leaves about 1 cup of juice remaining.
Add all ingredients and stir together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve warm.

title: confetti rice squares
directions: Combine
ingredients;
spoon
into
a
buttered
8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
May serve with cream of chicken on top.
Nice accompaniment to any meal.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and cover with lime water, using crock or plastic container (not metal).
Let stand for approximately 24 hours.
Drain cucumbers and cover with mixture made of vinegar, spice and sugar and let soak overnight.
Next morning, simmer for 25 to 30 minutes and seal in sterilized jars.
(Do not cover while cooking.)

title: mocha slices
directions: In a small cup stir together coffee crystals and water until dissolved.
In a large bowl beat 1/2 cup shortening and butter until soft.
Add about half of the flour and all of the sugar, cocoa, egg, milk, vanilla, cinnamon, baking soda and salt to mixture.
Add the coffee mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in remaining flour.
Shape dough into two (8-inch) rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill for 4 to 24 hours.
Cut dough into 1/8 inch thick slices.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes or until tops look dry.
Do not overbake.
Remove cookies and cool.
In saucepan heat chocolate chips and 1/4 cup shortening over low heat until melted together.
Dip half of each cookie in chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper and let stand until cookies set.

title: chicken and broccoli pasta in tomato cream sauce
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute broccoli in 2 tablespoons olive oil over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Drain tomatoes and cut into broccoli and mushrooms. Add cream, tomato paste and seasoning.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Saute chicken in rest of olive oil until done.
Add to vegetable sauce.
Serve over cooked rigatoni with Parmesan cheese.

title: fried rice with chicken
directions: Make an omelet with the eggs and cut it into strips, 1-inch long and 1/4-inch wide.
Set aside.

title: delightfully sinful cake
directions: Mix the cake mix as directed on box.
Bake for 28 minutes; cool slightly.
Punch holes in top of cake with sucker stick. Pour the caramel topping and sweetened condensed milk over top of cake.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream and toffee pieces.

title: flo's emerald forest cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In bowl, blend softened cream cheese with salt, dill seed, hot red pepper sauce, scallions, lemon juice and milk.
Mix well with fork and blend in chopped shrimp.
Cover and chill until serving.

title: okie cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour.
In a saucepan, bring to boil the shortening, butter, water and cocoa.
Pour over flour mixture while still hot.
Add the buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake in large cookie sheet with sides at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While baking, make icing.

title: dark chocolate frosting
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until frosting comes to a bubble for a short time.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Will frost 8 or 9-inch cake.
Double for a 9 x 13-inch cake or Bundt cake.
This is a chocolate lover's frosting.

title: never fail fudge
directions: In a 10 x 8 inch dish, mix sugar and cocoa, drop butter in, pour in milk.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on high stir lightly. Stir in nuts, add vanilla, stir.
Evenly spread fudge in dish. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Can add in 1/2 c peanut butter.

title: sweet potato praline
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, 1/2 cup margarine, milk and vanilla in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes in preheated 350° oven..
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar, flour, salt, Karo, vanilla, pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour in unbaked pastry shell and bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add cornstarch or flour and stir.
Slowly add milk; stir until thick and smooth.
Set aside.
Cut cabbage in two-inch pieces.
Boil in salted water about 15 minutes, then drain.
Set aside.
Add grated cheese and seasoning to white sauce.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: stroganoff loaf
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in water, sour cream, olives and seasoning mix. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Toast bread under broiler until golden.
Spread cut surface with butter. Spread half of meat mixture on each half of bread.
Arrange green pepper slices alternately with cherry tomatoes on top.

title: graham cracker candy
directions: Mix and
shape
graham
crumbs, powdered sugar, coconut, peanut butter and melted butter into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls and cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve first 3 items and mix well.
Add next 3 items.
Mix well and chill.

title: zucchini, carrot, corn saute
directions: Sprinkle salt on zucchini; let set 30 minutes.
Rinse with cold water; press between paper towels to remove water.
Heat butter and oil in a large skillet on medium heat.
Saute zucchini, corn and carrots until crisp-tender (4 to 5 minutes).
Add pepper and salt; sprinkle with onions.

title: magic steak strips
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch strips.
Dip in buttermilk, then in flour and back in buttermilk and flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fry in hot oil until brown and tender.
Serve with salad and baked potatoes and watch them disappear like magic.

title: cookies from southern germany
directions: Knead all ingredients together.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Form roll, cut in slices, roll and shape dough.
"S" is the traditional form.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 10 minutes.

title: opal's best cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add eggs, vanilla, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased (unfloured) 9 x 13-inch cake pan.	Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crumbly cheese cookies
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Flatten balls slightly with fork. Bake on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Yields approximately 50 cookies.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Put in colander and let drain.
Add all ingredients except salad dressing and cook for 30 minutes.
Remove from fire; cool and add salad dressing.
Mix well and seal.

title: currant and raspberry jam
directions: Wash currants; remove from stems.
Add raspberries, water and sugar.
Let stand for one hour.
Boil gently for 45 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: tuna and vegi sandwich
directions: Drain oil from tuna into a 1-cup glass measure.
Take 1/4 cup oil.
Add vinegar and garlic and beat with fork until blended.
Cut loaf in half horizontally.
Pull some bread from the center of each half to form a hollow, about 1-inch deep.
Spoon oil mixture over both sides.

title: orange egg nog
directions: Beat eggs extra good, about 10 minutes.
Add sugar gradually. Add flavorings and lemon juice and continue beating.
Mix orange juice and whipping cream in punch bowl.
Add egg mixture and mix well.
Add ice cream last.
Serves 25 cups.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine the sugar, vinegar, salad dressing, salt and milk in mixing bowl and beat until blended.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a large bowl and pour the dressing over all, then toss well.
Let stand for at least 20 minutes, then cool in refrigerator.

title: cheddar garden pasta
directions: In a covered saucepan, in 1/2-inch boiling water, cook carrots until tender; drain.
In same saucepan heat margarine over low heat.
Cook basil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add carrots and pasta; toss to coat.
Yields 6 servings.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight. Make into a roll. Roll in 3/4 cup chopped pecans and 3 tablespoons parsley.

title: hobo stew
directions: For children to make.

title: relish
directions: Heat to boiling the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and let set overnight.
